60Address AddressOf(const StackHandler* handler) {
61 Address raw = handler->address();
62#ifdef V8_USE_ADDRESS_SANITIZER
63 // ASan puts C++-allocated StackHandler markers onto its fake stack.
64 // We work around that by storing the real stack address in the "padding"
65 // field. StackHandlers allocated from generated code have 0 as padding.
66 Address padding =
67 base::Memory<Address>(raw + StackHandlerConstants::kPaddingOffset);
68 if (padding != 0) return padding;
69#endif
70 return raw;
71}

75// Iterator that supports traversing the stack handlers of a
76// particular frame. Needs to know the top of the handler chain.
77class StackHandlerIterator {
78 public:
79 StackHandlerIterator(const StackFrame* frame, StackHandler* handler)
80 : limit_(frame->fp()), handler_(handler) {
81#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
82#if !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE && !USE_SIMULATOR
83 // Make sure the handler has already been unwound to this frame. With stack
84 // switching this is not equivalent to the inequality below, because the
85 // frame and the handler could be in different stacks.
86 DCHECK_IMPLIES(frame->isolate()->wasm_stacks().empty(),
87 frame->InFastCCall() || frame->sp() <= AddressOf(handler));
88#endif // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE || !USE_SIMULATOR
89
90 // For CWasmEntry frames, the handler was registered by the last C++
91 // frame (Execution::CallWasm), so even though its address is already
92 // beyond the limit, we know we always want to unwind one handler.
93 if (frame->is_c_wasm_entry()) {
94 handler_ = handler_->next();
95#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
96 // Do the same for GenericWasmToJsInterpreterWrapper frames.
97 } else if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless && frame->is_wasm_to_js()) {
98 handler_ = handler_->next();
99#ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
100 // If we are running in the simulator, the handler_ address here will
101 // refer to the 'actual' stack, not to the 'simulated' stack, so we need
102 // to fix 'limit_' to make sure that the StackHandlerIterator won't skip
103 // any handler.
104 limit_ = 0;
105#endif // USE_SIMULATOR
106#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
107 }
108#else
109 // Make sure the handler has already been unwound to this frame.
110 DCHECK_LE(frame->sp(), AddressOf(handler));
111#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
112 }
113
114 StackHandler* handler() const { return handler_; }
115
116 bool done() { return handler_ == nullptr || AddressOf(handler_) > limit_; }
117 void Advance() {
118 DCHECK(!done());
119 handler_ = handler_->next();
120 }
121
122 private:
123#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE && USE_SIMULATOR
124 Address limit_;
125#else
126 const Address limit_;
127#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE && USE_SIMULATOR
128
129 StackHandler* handler_;
130};

174void StackFrameIterator::Advance() {
175 DCHECK(!done());
176 // Compute the state of the calling frame before restoring
177 // callee-saved registers and unwinding handlers. This allows the
178 // frame code that computes the caller state to access the top
179 // handler and the value of any callee-saved register if needed.
180 StackFrame::State state;
181 StackFrame::Type type;
182#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
183 if (frame_->type() == StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH &&
184 Memory<Address>(frame_->fp() +
185 StackSwitchFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset) ==
186 kNullAddress &&
187 !first_stack_only_) {
188 // Handle stack switches here.
189 // Note: both the "callee" frame (outermost frame of the child stack) and
190 // the "caller" frame (top frame of the parent stack) have frame type
191 // STACK_SWITCH. We use the caller FP to distinguish them: the callee frame
192 // does not have a caller fp.
193 auto parent = continuation()->parent();
194 CHECK(!IsUndefined(parent));
195 set_continuation(
196 GCSafeCast<WasmContinuationObject>(parent, isolate_->heap()));
197 wasm_stack_ = reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(continuation()->stack());
198 CHECK_EQ(wasm_stack_->jmpbuf()->state, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
199 StackSwitchFrame::GetStateForJumpBuffer(wasm_stack_->jmpbuf(), &state);
200 SetNewFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH, &state);
201 return;
202 }
203#endif
204 type = frame_->GetCallerState(&state);
205
206 // {StackHandlerIterator} assumes that frame pointers strictly go from lower
207 // to higher addresses as we iterate the stack. This breaks with
208 // stack-switching, so only unwind the stack handlers for frames that are
209 // known to use them.
210 if (frame_->type() == StackFrame::ENTRY ||
211 frame_->type() == StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY
212#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
213 || frame_->type() == StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY
214#endif
215 ) {
216 StackHandlerIterator it(frame_, handler_);
217 while (!it.done()) it.Advance();
218 handler_ = it.handler();
219 }
220
221 // Advance to the calling frame.
222 SetNewFrame(type, &state);
223 // When we're done iterating over the stack frames, the handler
224 // chain must have been completely unwound. Except if we are only iterating
225 // the first stack of the chain for wasm stack-switching.
226#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
227 DCHECK_IMPLIES(done() && !first_stack_only_, handler_ == nullptr);
228#else
229 DCHECK_IMPLIES(done(), handler_ == nullptr);
230#endif
231}

233StackFrame* StackFrameIterator::Reframe() {
234 StackFrame::State state = frame_->state_;
235 StackFrame::Type type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
236 SetNewFrame(type, &state);
237 return frame();
238}

240namespace {
241StackFrame::Type GetStateForFastCCallCallerFP(Isolate* isolate, Address fp,
242 Address pc, Address pc_address,
243 StackFrame::State* state) {
244 // 'Fast C calls' are a special type of C call where we call directly from
245 // JS to C without an exit frame inbetween. The CEntryStub is responsible
246 // for setting Isolate::c_entry_fp, meaning that it won't be set for fast C
247 // calls. To keep the stack iterable, we store the FP and PC of the caller
248 // of the fast C call on the isolate. This is guaranteed to be the topmost
249 // JS frame, because fast C calls cannot call back into JS. We start
250 // iterating the stack from this topmost JS frame.
251 DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, pc);
252 state->fp = fp;
253 state->sp = kNullAddress;
254 state->pc_address = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(pc_address);
255 state->callee_pc = kNullAddress;
256 state->constant_pool_address = nullptr;
257#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
258 if (wasm::WasmCode* code =
259 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate, pc)) {
260 if (code->kind() == wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper) {
261 return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS;
262 }
263 DCHECK_EQ(code->kind(), wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction);
264 return StackFrame::WASM;
265 }
266#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
267 return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
268}
269} // namespace

271void StackFrameIterator::Reset(ThreadLocalTop* top) {
272 StackFrame::State state;
273 StackFrame::Type type;
274
275 const Address fast_c_call_caller_fp =
276 isolate_->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_fp();
277 if (fast_c_call_caller_fp != kNullAddress) {
278 const Address caller_pc = isolate_->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc();
279 const Address caller_pc_address =
280 isolate_->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc_address();
281 type = GetStateForFastCCallCallerFP(isolate_, fast_c_call_caller_fp,
282 caller_pc, caller_pc_address, &state);
283 } else {
284 type = ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(Isolate::c_entry_fp(top), &state);
285 }
286#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
287 auto active_continuation = isolate_->root(RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
288 if (!IsUndefined(active_continuation, isolate_)) {
289 auto continuation = GCSafeCast<WasmContinuationObject>(active_continuation,
290 isolate_->heap());
291 if (!first_stack_only_) {
292 set_continuation(continuation);
293 }
294 wasm_stack_ = reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(continuation->stack());
295 }
296#endif
297 handler_ = StackHandler::FromAddress(Isolate::handler(top));
298 SetNewFrame(type, &state);
299}
300
301#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
302void StackFrameIterator::Reset(ThreadLocalTop* top, wasm::StackMemory* stack) {
303 if (stack->jmpbuf()->state == wasm::JumpBuffer::Retired) {
304 return;
305 }
306 StackFrame::State state;
307 StackSwitchFrame::GetStateForJumpBuffer(stack->jmpbuf(), &state);
308 handler_ = StackHandler::FromAddress(Isolate::handler(top));
309 wasm_stack_ = stack;
310 SetNewFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH, &state);
311}
312#endif

314void StackFrameIteratorBase::SetNewFrame(StackFrame::Type type,
315 StackFrame::State* state) {
316 SetNewFrame(type);
317 DCHECK_EQ(!frame_, type == StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
318 if (frame_) frame_->state_ = *state;
319}
320
321void StackFrameIteratorBase::SetNewFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
322 switch (type) {
323#define FRAME_TYPE_CASE(type, class) \
324 case StackFrame::type: \
325 frame_ = new (&class##_) class(this); \
326 return;
327 STACK_FRAME_TYPE_LIST(FRAME_TYPE_CASE)
328#undef FRAME_TYPE_CASE
329
330 case StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE:
331 // We don't expect to see NUMBER_OF_TYPES or MANUAL, but stay robust against
332 // them rather than being UNREACHABLE in case stack frame iteration gets
333 // wonky.
334 case StackFrame::NUMBER_OF_TYPES:
335 case StackFrame::MANUAL:
336 break;
337 }
338 frame_ = nullptr;
339}

365void ConstructFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
366 // The frame contains the actual argument count (intptr) that should not
367 // be visited.
368 FullObjectSlot argc(
369 &Memory<Address>(fp() + ConstructFrameConstants::kLengthOffset));
370 const int last_object_offset = ConstructFrameConstants::kLastObjectOffset;
371 FullObjectSlot base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
372 FullObjectSlot limit(&Memory<Address>(fp() + last_object_offset) + 1);
373 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, base, argc);
374 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, argc + 1, limit);
375 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), GcSafeLookupCode());
376}

418int DebuggableStackFrameIterator::FrameFunctionCount() const {
419 DCHECK(!done());
420 if (!iterator_.frame()->is_optimized_js()) return 1;
421 std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>> infos;
422 TurbofanJSFrame::cast(iterator_.frame())->GetFunctions(&infos);
423 return static_cast<int>(infos.size());

426FrameSummary DebuggableStackFrameIterator::GetTopValidFrame() const {
427 DCHECK(!done());
428 // Like FrameSummary::GetTop, but additionally observes
429 // DebuggableStackFrameIterator filtering semantics.
430 FrameSummaries summaries = frame()->Summarize();
431 if (is_javascript()) {
432 for (int i = summaries.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
433 const FrameSummary& summary = summaries.frames[i];
434 if (summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) {
435 return summary;
436 }
437 }
438 UNREACHABLE();
439 }
440#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
441 if (is_wasm()) return summaries.frames.back();
442#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
443 UNREACHABLE();
444}

446// static
447bool DebuggableStackFrameIterator::IsValidFrame(StackFrame* frame) {
448 if (frame->is_javascript()) {
449 Tagged<JSFunction> function =
450 static_cast<JavaScriptFrame*>(frame)->function();
451 return function->shared()->IsSubjectToDebugging();
452 }
453#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
454 if (frame->is_wasm()) return true;
455#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
456 return false;
457}

461namespace {

463std::optional<bool> IsInterpreterFramePc(Isolate* isolate, Address pc,
464 StackFrame::State* state) {
465 Builtin builtin = OffHeapInstructionStream::TryLookupCode(isolate, pc);
466 if (builtin != Builtin::kNoBuiltinId &&
467 (builtin == Builtin::kInterpreterEntryTrampoline ||
468 builtin == Builtin::kInterpreterEnterAtBytecode ||
469 builtin == Builtin::kInterpreterEnterAtNextBytecode)) {
470 return true;
471 } else if (isolate->interpreted_frames_native_stack()) {
472 intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(
473 state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
474 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
475 state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset,
476 kSystemPointerSize);
477 Tagged<Object> maybe_function = Tagged<Object>(
478 Memory<Address>(state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
479 // There's no need to run a full ContainsSlow if we know the frame can't be
480 // an InterpretedFrame, so we do these fast checks first
481 if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker) || IsSmi(maybe_function)) {
482 return false;
483 } else if (!isolate->heap()->InSpaceSlow(pc, CODE_SPACE)) {
484 return false;
485 }
486 if (!ThreadIsolation::CanLookupStartOfJitAllocationAt(pc)) {
487 return {};
488 }
489 Tagged<Code> interpreter_entry_trampoline =
490 isolate->heap()->FindCodeForInnerPointer(pc);
491 return interpreter_entry_trampoline->is_interpreter_trampoline_builtin();
492 } else {
493 return false;
494 }
495}

497} // namespace

499bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsNoFrameBytecodeHandlerPc(
500 Isolate* isolate, Address pc, Address fp) const {
501 EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob(isolate);
502 if (pc < d.InstructionStartOfBytecodeHandlers() ||
503 pc >= d.InstructionEndOfBytecodeHandlers()) {
504 return false;
505 }
506
507 Address frame_type_address =
508 fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset;
509 if (!IsValidStackAddress(frame_type_address)) {
510 return false;
511 }
512
513 // Check if top stack frame is a bytecode handler stub frame.
514 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(frame_type_address, kSystemPointerSize);
515 intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(frame_type_address);
516 if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker) &&
517 StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker) == StackFrame::STUB) {
518 // Bytecode handler built a frame.
519 return false;
520 }
521 return true;
522}
523
524StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::StackFrameIteratorForProfiler(
525 Isolate* isolate, Address pc, Address fp, Address sp, Address lr,
526 Address js_entry_sp)
527 : StackFrameIteratorBase(isolate),
528 low_bound_(sp),
529 high_bound_(js_entry_sp),
530 top_frame_type_(StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE),
531 external_callback_scope_(isolate->external_callback_scope()),
532 top_link_register_(lr)
533#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
534 ,
535 wasm_stacks_(isolate->wasm_stacks())
536#endif
537{
538 if (!isolate->isolate_data()->stack_is_iterable()) {
539 // The stack is not iterable in a short time interval during deoptimization.
540 // See also: ExternalReference::stack_is_iterable_address.
541 DCHECK(done());
542 return;
543 }
544
545 // For Advance below, we need frame_ to be set; and that only happens if the
546 // type is not NO_FRAME_TYPE.
547 // TODO(jgruber): Clean this up.
548 static constexpr StackFrame::Type kTypeForAdvance = StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
549
550 StackFrame::State state;
551 state.is_profiler_entry_frame = true;
552 StackFrame::Type type;
553 ThreadLocalTop* const top = isolate->thread_local_top();
554 bool advance_frame = true;
555 const Address fast_c_fp = isolate->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_fp();
556 if (fast_c_fp != kNullAddress) {
557 // 'Fast C calls' are a special type of C call where we call directly from
558 // JS to C without an exit frame inbetween. The CEntryStub is responsible
559 // for setting Isolate::c_entry_fp, meaning that it won't be set for fast C
560 // calls. To keep the stack iterable, we store the FP and PC of the caller
561 // of the fast C call on the isolate. This is guaranteed to be the topmost
562 // JS frame, because fast C calls cannot call back into JS. We start
563 // iterating the stack from this topmost JS frame.
564 DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, isolate->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc());
565 state.fp = fast_c_fp;
566 state.sp = sp;
567 state.pc_address = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
568 isolate->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc_address());
569
570 // ComputeStackFrameType will read both kContextOffset and
571 // kFunctionOffset, we check only that kFunctionOffset is within the stack
572 // bounds and do a compile time check that kContextOffset slot is pushed on
573 // the stack before kFunctionOffset.
574 static_assert(StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset <
575 StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset);
576 if (IsValidStackAddress(state.fp +
577 StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset)) {
578 type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
579 if (IsValidFrameType(type)) {
580 top_frame_type_ = type;
581 advance_frame = false;
582 }
583 } else {
584 // Cannot determine the actual type; the frame will be skipped below.
585 type = kTypeForAdvance;
586 }
587 } else if (IsValidTop(top)) {
588 type = ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(Isolate::c_entry_fp(top), &state);
589 top_frame_type_ = type;
590 } else if (IsValidStackAddress(fp)) {
591 DCHECK_NE(fp, kNullAddress);
592 state.fp = fp;
593 state.sp = sp;
594 state.pc_address =
595 StackFrame::ResolveReturnAddressLocation(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
596 fp + StandardFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
597
598 bool can_lookup_frame_type =
599 // Ensure frame structure is not broken, otherwise it doesn't make
600 // sense to try to detect a frame type.
601 (sp < fp) &&
602 // Ensure there is a context/frame type value in the frame.
603 (fp - sp) >= TypedFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
604
605 // If the current PC is in a bytecode handler, the top stack frame isn't
606 // the bytecode handler's frame and the top of stack or link register is a
607 // return address into the interpreter entry trampoline, then we are likely
608 // in a bytecode handler with elided frame. In that case, set the PC
609 // properly and make sure we do not drop the frame.
610 bool is_no_frame_bytecode_handler = false;
611 if (can_lookup_frame_type && IsNoFrameBytecodeHandlerPc(isolate, pc, fp)) {
612 Address* top_location = nullptr;
613 if (top_link_register_) {
614 top_location = &top_link_register_;
615 } else if (IsValidStackAddress(sp)) {
616 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(sp, kSystemPointerSize);
617 top_location = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(sp);
618 }
619
620 std::optional<bool> is_interpreter_frame_pc =
621 IsInterpreterFramePc(isolate, *top_location, &state);
622 // Since we're in a signal handler, the pc lookup might not be possible
623 // since the required locks are taken by the same thread.
624 if (!is_interpreter_frame_pc.has_value()) {
625 can_lookup_frame_type = false;
626 } else if (is_interpreter_frame_pc.value()) {
627 state.pc_address = top_location;
628 is_no_frame_bytecode_handler = true;
629 advance_frame = false;
630 }
631 }
632
633 // ComputeStackFrameType will read both kContextOffset and
634 // kFunctionOffset, we check only that kFunctionOffset is within the stack
635 // bounds and do a compile time check that kContextOffset slot is pushed on
636 // the stack before kFunctionOffset.
637 static_assert(StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset <
638 StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset);
639 Address function_slot = fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset;
640 if (!can_lookup_frame_type) {
641 type = StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
642 } else if (IsValidStackAddress(function_slot)) {
643 if (is_no_frame_bytecode_handler) {
644 type = StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
645 } else {
646 type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
647 }
648 top_frame_type_ = type;
649 } else {
650 // Cannot determine the actual type; the frame will be skipped below.
651 type = kTypeForAdvance;
652 }
653 } else {
654 // Not iterable.
655 DCHECK(done());
656 return;
657 }
658
659 SetNewFrame(type, &state);
660 if (advance_frame && !done()) {
661 Advance();
662 }
663}
664
665bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsValidTop(ThreadLocalTop* top) const {
666 Address c_entry_fp = Isolate::c_entry_fp(top);
667 if (!IsValidExitFrame(c_entry_fp)) return false;
668 // There should be at least one JS_ENTRY stack handler.
669 Address handler = Isolate::handler(top);
670 if (handler == kNullAddress) return false;
671 // Check that there are no js frames on top of the native frames.
672 return c_entry_fp < handler;
673}
674
675void StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::AdvanceOneFrame() {
676 DCHECK(!done());
677 StackFrame* last_frame = frame_;
678 Address last_sp = last_frame->sp(), last_fp = last_frame->fp();
679
680 // Before advancing to the next stack frame, perform pointer validity tests.
681 if (!IsValidState(last_frame->state_) ||
682 !HasValidExitIfEntryFrame(last_frame)) {
683 frame_ = nullptr;
684 return;
685 }
686
687 // Advance to the previous frame, and perform pointer validity tests there
688 // too.
689 StackFrame::State state;
690 last_frame->ComputeCallerState(&state);
691 if (!IsValidState(state)) {
692 frame_ = nullptr;
693 return;
694 }
695
696 StackFrame::Type type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
697 SetNewFrame(type, &state);
698 if (!frame_) return;
699
700 // Check that we have actually moved to the previous frame in the stack.
701 if (frame_->sp() <= last_sp || frame_->fp() <= last_fp) {
702 frame_ = nullptr;
703 }
704}
705
706bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsValidState(
707 const StackFrame::State& state) const {
708 return IsValidStackAddress(state.sp) && IsValidStackAddress(state.fp);
709}
710
711bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::HasValidExitIfEntryFrame(
712 const StackFrame* frame) const {
713 if (!frame->is_entry() && !frame->is_construct_entry()) return true;
714
715 // See EntryFrame::GetCallerState. It computes the caller FP address
716 // and calls ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer on it. We need to be
717 // sure that caller FP address is valid.
718 Address next_exit_frame_fp_address =
719 frame->fp() + EntryFrameConstants::kNextExitFrameFPOffset;
720 // Profiling tick might be triggered in the middle of JSEntry builtin
721 // before the next_exit_frame_fp value is initialized. IsValidExitFrame()
722 // is able to deal with such a case, so just suppress the MSan warning.
723 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(next_exit_frame_fp_address, kSystemPointerSize);
724 Address next_exit_frame_fp = Memory<Address>(next_exit_frame_fp_address);
725 return IsValidExitFrame(next_exit_frame_fp);
726}
727
728bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsValidExitFrame(Address fp) const {
729 if (!IsValidStackAddress(fp)) return false;
730 Address sp = ExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp);
731 if (!IsValidStackAddress(sp)) return false;
732 StackFrame::State state;
733 ExitFrame::FillState(fp, sp, &state);
734 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(state.pc_address, sizeof(state.pc_address));
735 return *state.pc_address != kNullAddress;
736}
737
738void StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::Advance() {
739 while (true) {
740 AdvanceOneFrame();
741 if (done()) break;
742 ExternalCallbackScope* last_callback_scope = nullptr;
743 while (external_callback_scope_ != nullptr &&
744 external_callback_scope_->JSStackComparableAddress() <
745 frame_->fp()) {
746 // As long as the setup of a frame is not atomic, we may happen to be
747 // in an interval where an ExternalCallbackScope is already created,
748 // but the frame is not yet entered. So we are actually observing
749 // the previous frame.
750 // Skip all the ExternalCallbackScope's that are below the current fp.
751 last_callback_scope = external_callback_scope_;
752 external_callback_scope_ = external_callback_scope_->previous();
753 }
754 if (frame_->is_javascript()) break;
755#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
756 if (frame_->is_wasm() || frame_->is_wasm_to_js() ||
757 frame_->is_js_to_wasm()) {
758 break;
759 }
760#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
761 if (frame_->is_exit() || frame_->is_builtin_exit() ||
762 frame_->is_api_accessor_exit() || frame_->is_api_callback_exit()) {
763 // Some of the EXIT frames may have ExternalCallbackScope allocated on
764 // top of them. In that case the scope corresponds to the first EXIT
765 // frame beneath it. There may be other EXIT frames on top of the
766 // ExternalCallbackScope, just skip them as we cannot collect any useful
767 // information about them.
768 if (last_callback_scope) {
769 frame_->state_.pc_address =
770 last_callback_scope->callback_entrypoint_address();
771 }
772 break;
773 }
774 }
775}

780 Address js_entry_sp)
781 : StackFrameIteratorForProfiler(isolate, pc, fp, sp, lr, js_entry_sp) {}
782
783void StackFrameIteratorForProfilerForTesting::Advance() {
784 StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::Advance();
785}

820
821void StackFrame::IteratePc(RootVisitor* v, Address* constant_pool_address,
822 Tagged<GcSafeCode> holder) const {
823 const Address old_pc = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
824 DCHECK_GE(old_pc, holder->InstructionStart(isolate(), old_pc));
825 DCHECK_LT(old_pc, holder->InstructionEnd(isolate(), old_pc));
826
827 // Keep the old pc offset before visiting the code since we need it to
828 // calculate the new pc after a potential InstructionStream move.
829 const uintptr_t pc_offset_from_start = old_pc - holder->instruction_start();
830
831 // Visit.
832 Tagged<GcSafeCode> visited_holder = holder;
833 PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base{isolate()->code_cage_base()};
834 const Tagged<Object> old_istream =
835 holder->raw_instruction_stream(code_cage_base);
836 Tagged<Object> visited_istream = old_istream;
837 v->VisitRunningCode(FullObjectSlot{&visited_holder},
838 FullObjectSlot{&visited_istream});
839 if (visited_istream == old_istream) {
840 // Note this covers two important cases:
841 // 1. the associated InstructionStream object did not move, and
842 // 2. `holder` is an embedded builtin and has no InstructionStream.
843 return;
844 }
845
846 DCHECK(visited_holder->has_instruction_stream());
847 // We can only relocate the InstructionStream object when we are able to patch
848 // the return address. We only know the location of the return address if the
849 // stack pointer is known. This means we cannot relocate InstructionStreams
850 // for fast c calls.
851 DCHECK(!InFastCCall());
852 // Currently we turn off code space compaction fully when performing a GC in a
853 // fast C call.
854 DCHECK(!isolate()->InFastCCall());
855
856 Tagged<InstructionStream> istream =
857 GCSafeCast<InstructionStream>(visited_istream, isolate()->heap());
858 const Address new_pc = istream->instruction_start() + pc_offset_from_start;
859 // TODO(v8:10026): avoid replacing a signed pointer.
860 PointerAuthentication::ReplacePC(pc_address(), new_pc, kSystemPointerSize);
861 if (V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL && constant_pool_address != nullptr) {
862 *constant_pool_address = istream->constant_pool();
863 }
864}

869 return_address_location_resolver_ = resolver;

874StackFrame::Type ComputeBuiltinFrameType(Tagged<GcSafeCode> code) {
875 if (code->is_interpreter_trampoline_builtin() ||
876 code->is_baseline_trampoline_builtin()) {
877 // Frames for baseline entry trampolines on the stack are still interpreted
878 // frames.
879 return StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
880 } else if (code->is_baseline_leave_frame_builtin()) {
881 return StackFrame::BASELINE;
882 } else if (code->is_turbofanned()) {
883 // TODO(bmeurer): We treat frames for BUILTIN Code objects as
884 // OptimizedJSFrame for now (all the builtins with JavaScript linkage are
885 // actually generated with TurboFan currently, so this is sound).
886 return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
887 }
888 return StackFrame::BUILTIN;
889}
890
891StackFrame::Type SafeStackFrameType(StackFrame::Type candidate) {
892 DCHECK_LE(static_cast<uintptr_t>(candidate), StackFrame::NUMBER_OF_TYPES);
893 switch (candidate) {
894 case StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT:
895 case StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT:
896 case StackFrame::BUILTIN_CONTINUATION:
897 case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:
898 case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT:
899 case StackFrame::FAST_CONSTRUCT:
900 case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY:
901 case StackFrame::ENTRY:
902 case StackFrame::EXIT:
903 case StackFrame::INTERNAL:
904 case StackFrame::IRREGEXP:
905 case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION:
906 case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH:
907 case StackFrame::STUB:
908 return candidate;
909
910#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
911 case StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM:
912 case StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH:
913 case StackFrame::WASM:
914 case StackFrame::WASM_DEBUG_BREAK:
915 case StackFrame::WASM_EXIT:
916 case StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP:
917 case StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS:
918 case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
919#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
920 case StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY:
921 case StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY:
922#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
923 return candidate;
924#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
925
926 // Any other marker value is likely to be a bogus stack frame when being
927 // called from the profiler (in particular, JavaScript frames, including
928 // interpreted frames, should never have a StackFrame::Type marker).
929 // Consider these frames "native".
930 // TODO(jgruber): For the StackFrameIterator, I'm not sure this fallback
931 // makes sense. Shouldn't we know how to handle all frames we encounter
932 // there?
933 case StackFrame::BASELINE:
934 case StackFrame::BUILTIN:
935 case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
936 case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
937 case StackFrame::MANUAL:
938 case StackFrame::NATIVE:
939 case StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE:
940 case StackFrame::NUMBER_OF_TYPES:
941 case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
942 case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_STUB_WITH_CONTEXT:
943#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
944#if !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
945 case StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY:
946#endif // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
947 case StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
948#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
949 return StackFrame::NATIVE;
950 }
951 UNREACHABLE();
952}
953
954} // namespace
955
956StackFrame::Type StackFrameIterator::ComputeStackFrameType(
957 StackFrame::State* state) const {
958#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
959 if (state->fp == kNullAddress && first_stack_only_) {
960 DCHECK(!isolate_->wasm_stacks().empty()); // I.e., JSPI active
961 return StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
962 }
963#endif
964
965 const Address pc = StackFrame::ReadPC(state->pc_address);
966
967#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
968 // If the {pc} does not point into WebAssembly code we can rely on the
969 // returned {wasm_code} to be null and fall back to {GetContainingCode}.
970 if (wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code =
971 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), pc)) {
972 switch (wasm_code->kind()) {
973 case wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction:
974 return StackFrame::WASM;
975 case wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToCapiWrapper:
976 return StackFrame::WASM_EXIT;
977 case wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper:
978 return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS;
979#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
980 case wasm::WasmCode::kInterpreterEntry:
981 return StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY;
982#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
983 default:
984 UNREACHABLE();
985 }
986 }
987#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
988
989 // Look up the code object to figure out the type of the stack frame.
990 std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> lookup_result =
991 GetContainingCode(isolate(), pc);
992 if (!lookup_result.has_value()) return StackFrame::NATIVE;
993
994 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
995 state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset,
996 kSystemPointerSize);
997 const intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(
998 state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
999 switch (lookup_result.value()->kind()) {
1000 case CodeKind::BUILTIN: {
1001 if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker)) break;
1002 return ComputeBuiltinFrameType(lookup_result.value());
1003 }
1004 case CodeKind::BASELINE:
1005 // Baseline code can be deoptimized by DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor.
1006 if (lookup_result.value()->marked_for_deoptimization())
1007 return StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
1008 return StackFrame::BASELINE;
1009 case CodeKind::MAGLEV:
1010 if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker)) {
1011 // An INTERNAL frame can be set up with an associated Maglev code
1012 // object when calling into runtime to handle tiering. In this case,
1013 // all stack slots are tagged pointers and should be visited through
1014 // the usual logic.
1015 DCHECK_EQ(StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker), StackFrame::INTERNAL);
1016 return StackFrame::INTERNAL;
1017 }
1018 return StackFrame::MAGLEV;
1019 case CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS:
1020 return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
1021#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1022 case CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION:
1023 if (lookup_result.value()->builtin_id() == Builtin::kJSToWasmWrapperAsm) {
1024 return StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM;
1025 }
1026#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1027 if (lookup_result.value()->builtin_id() ==
1028 Builtin::kGenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper) {
1029 return StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM;
1030 }
1031#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1032 return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_STUB_WITH_CONTEXT;
1033 case CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY:
1034 return StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY;
1035 case CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
1036 return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION;
1037 case CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION:
1038 case CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION:
1039 // These never appear as on-heap Code objects.
1040 UNREACHABLE();
1041#else
1042 case CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY:
1043 case CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION:
1044 case CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION:
1045 case CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION:
1046 case CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
1047 UNREACHABLE();
1048#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1049 case CodeKind::BYTECODE_HANDLER:
1050 case CodeKind::FOR_TESTING:
1051 case CodeKind::REGEXP:
1052 case CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION:
1053 // Fall back to the marker.
1054 break;
1055 }
1056
1057 return SafeStackFrameType(StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker));
1058}
1059
1060StackFrame::Type StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::ComputeStackFrameType(
1061 StackFrame::State* state) const {
1062#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1063 if (state->fp == kNullAddress) {
1064 DCHECK(!isolate_->wasm_stacks().empty()); // I.e., JSPI active
1065 return StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
1066 }
1067#endif
1068
1069 // We use unauthenticated_pc because it may come from
1070 // fast_c_call_caller_pc_address, for which authentication does not work.
1071 const Address pc = StackFrame::unauthenticated_pc(state->pc_address);
1072#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1073 Tagged<Code> wrapper =
1074 isolate()->builtins()->code(Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA);
1075 if (pc >= wrapper->instruction_start() && pc <= wrapper->instruction_end()) {
1076 return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS;
1077 }
1078#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1079
1080 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
1081 state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset,
1082 kSystemPointerSize);
1083 const intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(
1084 state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
1085 if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker)) {
1086 return SafeStackFrameType(StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker));
1087 }
1088
1089 MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
1090 state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset, kSystemPointerSize);
1091 Tagged<Object> maybe_function = Tagged<Object>(
1092 Memory<Address>(state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
1093 if (IsSmi(maybe_function)) {
1094 return StackFrame::NATIVE;
1095 }
1096
1097 std::optional<bool> is_interpreter_frame =
1098 IsInterpreterFramePc(isolate(), pc, state);
1099
1100 // We might not be able to lookup the frame type since we're inside a signal
1101 // handler and the required locks are taken.
1102 if (!is_interpreter_frame.has_value()) {
1103 return StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
1104 }
1105
1106 if (is_interpreter_frame.value()) {
1107 return StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
1108 }
1109
1110 return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
1111}

1175void ExitFrame::ComputeCallerState(State* state) const {
1176 // Set up the caller state.
1177 state->sp = caller_sp();

1188void ExitFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
1189 // The arguments are traversed as part of the expression stack of
1190 // the calling frame.
1191 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), GcSafeLookupCode());
1192}
1193
1194StackFrame::Type ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(Address fp, State* state) {
1195 if (fp == 0) return NO_FRAME_TYPE;
1196 StackFrame::Type type = ComputeFrameType(fp);
1197#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1198 Address sp = type == WASM_EXIT ? WasmExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp)
1199 : ExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp);
1200#else
1201 Address sp = ExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp);
1202#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1203 FillState(fp, sp, state);
1204 DCHECK_NE(*state->pc_address, kNullAddress);
1205 return type;
1206}
1207
1208StackFrame::Type ExitFrame::ComputeFrameType(Address fp) {
1209 // Distinguish between different exit frame types.
1210 // Default to EXIT in all hairy cases (e.g., when called from profiler).
1211 const int offset = ExitFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset;
1212 Tagged<Object> marker(Memory<Address>(fp + offset));
1213
1214 if (!IsSmi(marker)) {
1215 return EXIT;
1216 }
1217
1218 intptr_t marker_int = base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(marker);
1219
1220 StackFrame::Type frame_type = static_cast<StackFrame::Type>(marker_int >> 1);
1221 switch (frame_type) {
1222 case BUILTIN_EXIT:
1223 case API_ACCESSOR_EXIT:
1224 case API_CALLBACK_EXIT:
1225#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1226 case WASM_EXIT:
1227 case STACK_SWITCH:
1228#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1229 return frame_type;
1230 default:
1231 return EXIT;
1232 }
1233}

1237 kSystemPointerSize);

1239}
1240
1241#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1242Address WasmExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(Address fp) {
1243 // For WASM_EXIT frames, {sp} is only needed for finding the PC slot,
1244 // everything else is handled via safepoint information.
1245 Address sp = fp + WasmExitFrameConstants::kWasmInstanceDataOffset;
1246 DCHECK_EQ(sp - 1 * kPCOnStackSize,
1247 fp + WasmExitFrameConstants::kCallingPCOffset);
1248 return sp;
1249}
1250#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1251
1252void ExitFrame::FillState(Address fp, Address sp, State* state) {
1253 state->sp = sp;
1254 state->fp = fp;
1255 state->pc_address = ResolveReturnAddressLocation(
1256 reinterpret_cast<Address*>(sp - 1 * kPCOnStackSize));
1257 state->callee_pc = kNullAddress;
1258 // The constant pool recorded in the exit frame is not associated
1259 // with the pc in this state (the return address into a C entry
1260 // stub). ComputeCallerState will retrieve the constant pool
1261 // together with the associated caller pc.
1262 state->constant_pool_address = nullptr;
1263}

1542void CommonFrame::ComputeCallerState(State* state) const {
1543 state->fp = caller_fp();
1544#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1545 if (state->fp == kNullAddress) {
1546 // An empty FP signals the first frame of a stack segment. The caller is
1547 // on a different stack, or is unbound (suspended stack).
1548 // DCHECK(isolate_->wasm_stacks() != nullptr); // I.e., JSPI active

1566namespace {
1567void VisitSpillSlot(Isolate* isolate, RootVisitor* v,
1568 FullObjectSlot spill_slot) {
1569#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1570 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
1571 bool was_compressed = false;
1572
1573 // Spill slots may contain compressed values in which case the upper
1574 // 32-bits will contain zeros. In order to simplify handling of such
1575 // slots in GC we ensure that the slot always contains full value.
1576
1577 // The spill slot may actually contain weak references so we load/store
1578 // values using spill_slot.location() in order to avoid dealing with
1579 // FullMaybeObjectSlots here.
1580 if (V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE_BOOL) {
1581 // When external code space is enabled the spill slot could contain both
1582 // InstructionStream and non-InstructionStream references, which have
1583 // different cage bases. So unconditional decompression of the value might
1584 // corrupt InstructionStream pointers. However, given that 1) the
1585 // InstructionStream pointers are never compressed by design (because
1586 // otherwise we wouldn't know which cage base to apply for
1587 // decompression, see respective DCHECKs in
1588 // RelocInfo::target_object()),
1589 // 2) there's no need to update the upper part of the full pointer
1590 // because if it was there then it'll stay the same,
1591 // we can avoid updating upper part of the spill slot if it already
1592 // contains full value.
1593 // TODO(v8:11880): Remove this special handling by enforcing builtins
1594 // to use CodeTs instead of InstructionStream objects.
1595 Address value = *spill_slot.location();
1596 if (!HAS_SMI_TAG(value) && value <= 0xffffffff) {
1597 // We don't need to update smi values or full pointers.
1598 was_compressed = true;
1599 *spill_slot.location() = V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
1600 cage_base, static_cast<Tagged_t>(value));
1601 if (DEBUG_BOOL) {
1602 // Ensure that the spill slot contains correct heap object.
1603 Tagged<HeapObject> raw =
1604 Cast<HeapObject>(Tagged<Object>(*spill_slot.location()));
1605 MapWord map_word = raw->map_word(cage_base, kRelaxedLoad);
1606 Tagged<HeapObject> forwarded = map_word.IsForwardingAddress()
1607 ? map_word.ToForwardingAddress(raw)
1608 : raw;
1609 bool is_self_forwarded =
1610 HeapLayout::IsSelfForwarded(forwarded, cage_base);
1611 if (is_self_forwarded) {
1612 // The object might be in a self-forwarding state if it's located
1613 // in new large object space. GC will fix this at a later stage.
1614 CHECK(
1615 MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(forwarded)->InNewLargeObjectSpace() ||
1616 MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(forwarded)->IsQuarantined());
1617 } else {
1618 Tagged<HeapObject> forwarded_map = forwarded->map(cage_base);
1619 // The map might be forwarded as well.
1620 MapWord fwd_map_map_word =
1621 forwarded_map->map_word(cage_base, kRelaxedLoad);
1622 if (fwd_map_map_word.IsForwardingAddress()) {
1623 forwarded_map = fwd_map_map_word.ToForwardingAddress(forwarded_map);
1624 }
1625 CHECK(IsMap(forwarded_map, cage_base));
1626 }
1627 }
1628 }
1629 } else {
1630 Address slot_contents = *spill_slot.location();
1631 Tagged_t compressed_value = static_cast<Tagged_t>(slot_contents);
1632 if (!HAS_SMI_TAG(compressed_value)) {
1633 was_compressed = slot_contents <= 0xFFFFFFFF;
1634 // We don't need to update smi values.
1635 *spill_slot.location() = V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
1636 cage_base, compressed_value);
1637 }
1638 }
1639#endif
1640 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot);
1641#if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1642 if (was_compressed) {
1643 // Restore compression. Generated code should be able to trust that
1644 // compressed spill slots remain compressed.
1645 *spill_slot.location() =
1646 V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(*spill_slot.location());
1647 }
1648#endif
1649}
1650
1651void VisitSpillSlots(Isolate* isolate, RootVisitor* v,
1652 FullObjectSlot first_slot_offset,
1653 base::Vector<const uint8_t> tagged_slots) {
1654 FullObjectSlot slot_offset = first_slot_offset;
1655 for (uint8_t bits : tagged_slots) {
1656 while (bits) {
1657 const int bit = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(bits);
1658 bits &= ~(1 << bit);
1659 FullObjectSlot spill_slot = slot_offset + bit;
1660 VisitSpillSlot(isolate, v, spill_slot);
1661 }
1662 slot_offset += kBitsPerByte;
1663 }
1664}

1700// Class DrumBrakeWasmCode is an adapter class that exposes just the accessors
1701// of the original WasmCode class that are used in WasmFrame::Iterate. For non
1702// DrumBrake frames, the class calls the corresponding accessor in a contained
1703// WasmCode object, while for DrumBrake frames it returns dummy values. This is
1704// useful to minimize the merge issues in WasmFrame::Iterate.
1705class DrumBrakeWasmCode {
1706 public:
1707 explicit DrumBrakeWasmCode(wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code)
1708 : wasm_code_(wasm_code) {}
1709
1710 static std::unique_ptr<DrumBrakeWasmCode> Interpreted() {
1711 return std::make_unique<DrumBrakeWasmCode>(nullptr);
1712 }
1713 static std::unique_ptr<DrumBrakeWasmCode> Compiled(
1714 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code) {
1715 return std::make_unique<DrumBrakeWasmCode>(wasm_code);
1716 }
1717
1718 bool is_liftoff() const {
1719 return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->is_liftoff() : false;
1720 }
1721 bool frame_has_feedback_slot() const {
1722 return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->frame_has_feedback_slot() : false;
1723 }
1724 int stack_slots() const { return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->stack_slots() : 0; }
1725 wasm::WasmCode::Kind kind() const {
1726 return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->kind() : wasm::WasmCode::kInterpreterEntry;
1727 }
1728 uint16_t first_tagged_parameter_slot() const {
1729 return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->first_tagged_parameter_slot() : 0;
1730 }
1731 uint16_t num_tagged_parameter_slots() const {
1732 return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->num_tagged_parameter_slots() : 0;
1733 }
1734
1735 private:
1736 const wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code_;
1737};
1738#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1739
1740void WasmFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
1741 DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
1742
1743 // === WasmFrame ===
1744 // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1745 // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
1746 // | ... |
1747 // | out_param 0 | (these can be tagged or untagged)
1748 // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1749 // | spill_slot n | <-- parameters_limit ^
1750 // | ... | spill_slot_space
1751 // | spill_slot 0 | v
1752 // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1753 // | WasmFeedback(*) | <-- frame_header_base ^
1754 // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1755 // | WasmTrustedInstanceData | |
1756 // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1757 // | Type Marker | |
1758 // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| frame_header_size
1759 // | [Constant Pool] | |
1760 // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1761 // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
1762 // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1763 // | return addr | <-- tagged_parameter_limit v
1764 // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1765 // | in_param n |
1766 // | ... |
1767 // | in_param 0 | <-- first_tagged_parameter_slot
1768 // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1769 //
1770 // (*) Only if compiled by Liftoff and with --wasm-inlining.
1771
1772#if !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1773 auto pair = wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCodeAndSafepoint(
1774 isolate(), maybe_unauthenticated_pc());
1775 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code = pair.first;
1776 SafepointEntry safepoint_entry = pair.second;
1777#else // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1778 std::unique_ptr<DrumBrakeWasmCode> interpreter_wasm_code;
1779 SafepointEntry safepoint_entry;
1780 bool is_wasm_interpreter_frame =
1781 v8_flags.wasm_jitless &&
1782 (type() == WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY || type() == C_WASM_ENTRY);
1783 if (is_wasm_interpreter_frame) {
1784 interpreter_wasm_code = DrumBrakeWasmCode::Interpreted();
1785 } else {
1786 auto pair =
1787 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCodeAndSafepoint(isolate(), pc());
1788 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code = pair.first;
1789 safepoint_entry = pair.second;
1790 DCHECK(wasm_code);
1791 interpreter_wasm_code = DrumBrakeWasmCode::Compiled(wasm_code);
1792 }
1793
1794 // Reuse the same name "wasm_code" for this variable, to use the
1795 // DrumBrakeWasmCode adapter and minimize merge issues in the following code.
1796 DrumBrakeWasmCode* wasm_code = interpreter_wasm_code.get();
1797#endif // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1798
1799#ifdef DEBUG
1800 intptr_t marker =
1801 Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
1802 DCHECK(StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
1803 StackFrame::Type type = StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker);
1804 DCHECK(type == WASM_TO_JS || type == WASM || type == WASM_EXIT ||
1805 type == WASM_SEGMENT_START);
1806#endif
1807
1808 // Determine the fixed header and spill slot area size.
1809 // The last value in the frame header is the calling PC, which should
1810 // not be visited.
1811 static_assert(WasmExitFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountFromFp ==
1812 WasmFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountFromFp + 1,
1813 "WasmExitFrame has one slot more than WasmFrame");
1814
1815 int frame_header_size = WasmFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
1816 if (wasm_code->is_liftoff() && wasm_code->frame_has_feedback_slot()) {
1817 // Frame has Wasm feedback slot.
1818 frame_header_size += kSystemPointerSize;
1819 }
1820 int spill_slot_space =
1821 wasm_code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize -
1822 (frame_header_size + StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp);
1823 // Fixed frame slots.
1824 FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() - frame_header_size));
1825 FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
1826 &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
1827
1828 // Visit parameters passed to the callee.
1829 // Frame layout without stack switching (stack grows upwards):
1830 //
1831 // | callee |
1832 // | frame |
1833 // |-------------| <- sp()
1834 // | out params |
1835 // |-------------| <- frame_header_base - spill_slot_space
1836 // | spill slots |
1837 // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
1838 // | frame header|
1839 // |-------------| <- fp()
1840 //
1841 // With stack-switching:
1842 //
1843 // Secondary stack: Central stack:
1844 //
1845 // | callee |
1846 // | frame |
1847 // |------------| <- sp()
1848 // | out params |
1849 // |-------------| |------------| <- maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
1850 // | spill slots |
1851 // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
1852 // | frame header|
1853 // |-------------| <- fp()
1854 //
1855 // The base (lowest address) of the outgoing stack parameters area is always
1856 // sp(), and the limit (highest address) is either {frame_header_base -
1857 // spill_slot_space} or {maybe_stack_switch.target_sp} depending on
1858 // stack-switching.
1859 wasm::StackMemory::StackSwitchInfo maybe_stack_switch;
1860 if (iterator_->wasm_stack() != nullptr) {
1861 maybe_stack_switch = iterator_->wasm_stack()->stack_switch_info();
1862 }
1863 FullObjectSlot parameters_limit(
1864 maybe_stack_switch.has_value() && maybe_stack_switch.source_fp == fp()
1865 ? maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
1866 : frame_header_base.address() - spill_slot_space);
1867 FullObjectSlot spill_space_end =
1868 FullObjectSlot(frame_header_base.address() - spill_slot_space);
1869
1870 // Visit the rest of the parameters if they are tagged.
1871 bool has_tagged_outgoing_params =
1872 wasm_code->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction &&
1873 wasm_code->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToCapiWrapper;
1874 if (!InFastCCall() && has_tagged_outgoing_params) {
1875 FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
1876 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
1877 parameters_limit);
1878 }
1879
1880 // Visit pointer spill slots and locals.
1881 if (safepoint_entry.is_initialized()) {
1882 DCHECK_GE((wasm_code->stack_slots() + kBitsPerByte) / kBitsPerByte,
1883 safepoint_entry.tagged_slots().size());
1884 VisitSpillSlots(isolate(), v, spill_space_end,
1885 safepoint_entry.tagged_slots());
1886 }
1887
1888 // Visit tagged parameters that have been passed to the function of this
1889 // frame. Conceptionally these parameters belong to the parent frame. However,
1890 // the exact count is only known by this frame (in the presence of tail calls,
1891 // this information cannot be derived from the call site).
1892 if (wasm_code->num_tagged_parameter_slots() > 0) {
1893 FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_base(&Memory<Address>(caller_sp()));
1894 tagged_parameter_base += wasm_code->first_tagged_parameter_slot();
1895 FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_limit =
1896 tagged_parameter_base + wasm_code->num_tagged_parameter_slots();
1897
1898 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, tagged_parameter_base,
1899 tagged_parameter_limit);
1900 }
1901
1902 // Visit the instance object.
1903 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base,
1904 frame_header_limit);
1905}
1906
1907void TypedFrame::IterateParamsOfGenericWasmToJSWrapper(RootVisitor* v) const {
1908 Address maybe_sig =
1909 Memory<Address>(fp() + WasmToJSWrapperConstants::kSignatureOffset);
1910 if (maybe_sig == 0 || maybe_sig == static_cast<Address>(-1)) {
1911 // The signature slot was reset after processing all incoming parameters.
1912 // We don't have to keep them alive anymore.
1913 return;
1914 }
1915
1916 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig =
1917 reinterpret_cast<wasm::CanonicalSig*>(maybe_sig);
1918 DCHECK(wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->Contains(sig));
1919 wasm::LinkageLocationAllocator allocator(wasm::kGpParamRegisters,
1920 wasm::kFpParamRegisters, 0);
1921 // The first parameter is the instance data, which we don't have to scan. We
1922 // have to tell the LinkageLocationAllocator about it though.
1923 allocator.Next(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
1924
1925 // Parameters are separated into two groups (first all untagged, then all
1926 // tagged parameters). Therefore we first have to iterate over the signature
1927 // first to process all untagged parameters, and afterwards we can scan the
1928 // tagged parameters.
1929 bool has_tagged_param = false;
1930 for (wasm::CanonicalValueType type : sig->parameters()) {
1931 MachineRepresentation param = type.machine_representation();
1932 // Skip tagged parameters (e.g. any-ref).
1933 if (IsAnyTagged(param)) {
1934 has_tagged_param = true;
1935 continue;
1936 }
1937 if (kSystemPointerSize == 8 || param != MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1938 allocator.Next(param);
1939 } else {
1940 allocator.Next(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1941 allocator.Next(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1942 }
1943 }
1944
1945 // End the untagged area, so tagged slots come after. This means, especially,
1946 // that tagged parameters should not fill holes in the untagged area.
1947 allocator.EndSlotArea();
1948
1949 if (!has_tagged_param) return;
1950
1951#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
1952 constexpr size_t size_of_sig = 2;
1953#else
1954 constexpr size_t size_of_sig = 1;
1955#endif
1956
1957 for (wasm::CanonicalValueType type : sig->parameters()) {
1958 MachineRepresentation param = type.machine_representation();
1959 // Skip untagged parameters.
1960 if (!IsAnyTagged(param)) continue;
1961 LinkageLocation l = allocator.Next(param);
1962 if (l.IsRegister()) {
1963 // Calculate the slot offset.
1964 int slot_offset = 0;
1965 // We have to do a reverse lookup in the kGPParamRegisters array. This
1966 // can be optimized if necessary.
1967 for (size_t i = 1; i < arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters); ++i) {
1968 if (wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i].code() == l.AsRegister()) {
1969 // The first register (the instance) does not get spilled.
1970 slot_offset = static_cast<int>(i) - 1;
1971 break;
1972 }
1973 }
1974 // Caller FP + return address + signature.
1975 size_t param_start_offset = 2 + size_of_sig;
1976 FullObjectSlot param_start(fp() +
1977 param_start_offset * kSystemPointerSize);
1978 FullObjectSlot tagged_slot = param_start + slot_offset;
1979 VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, tagged_slot);
1980 } else {
1981 // Caller frame slots have negative indices and start at -1. Flip it
1982 // back to a positive offset (to be added to the frame's FP to find the
1983 // slot).
1984 int slot_offset = -l.GetLocation() - 1;
1985 // Caller FP + return address + signature + spilled registers (without the
1986 // instance register).
1987 size_t slots_per_float64 = kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize;
1988 size_t param_start_offset =
1989 arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) - 1 +
1990 (arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters) * slots_per_float64) + 2 +
1991 size_of_sig;
1992
1993 // The wasm-to-js wrapper pushes all but the first gp parameter register
1994 // on the stack, so if the number of gp parameter registers is even, this
1995 // means that the wrapper pushed an odd number. In that case, and when the
1996 // size of a double on the stack is two words, then there is an alignment
1997 // word between the pushed gp registers and the pushed fp registers, so
1998 // that the whole spill area is double-size aligned.
1999 if (arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) % 2 == (0) &&
2000 kSystemPointerSize != kDoubleSize) {
2001 param_start_offset++;
2002 }
2003 FullObjectSlot param_start(fp() +
2004 param_start_offset * kSystemPointerSize);
2005 FullObjectSlot tagged_slot = param_start + slot_offset;
2006 VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, tagged_slot);
2007 }
2008 }
2009}

2011void TypedFrame::IterateParamsOfOptimizedWasmToJSWrapper(RootVisitor* v) const {
2012 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = GcSafeLookupCode();
2013 if (code->wasm_js_tagged_parameter_count() > 0) {
2014 FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_base(&Memory<Address>(caller_sp()));
2015 tagged_parameter_base += code->wasm_js_first_tagged_parameter();
2016 FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_limit =
2017 tagged_parameter_base + code->wasm_js_tagged_parameter_count();
2018 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, tagged_parameter_base,
2019 tagged_parameter_limit);
2020 }
2021}
2022#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2023
2024void TypedFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
2025 DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
2026
2027 // === TypedFrame ===
2028 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2029 // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
2030 // | ... |
2031 // | out_param 0 |
2032 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2033 // | spill_slot n | <-- parameters_limit ^
2034 // | ... | spill_slot_count
2035 // | spill_slot 0 | v
2036 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2037 // | Type Marker | <-- frame_header_base ^
2038 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2039 // | [Constant Pool] | |
2040 // |- - - - - - - - -| kFixedSlotCount
2041 // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
2042 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2043 // | return addr | v
2044 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2045
2046 // Find the code and compute the safepoint information.
2047 Address inner_pointer = pc();
2048 InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
2049 isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(inner_pointer);
2050 CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
2051 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
2052#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2053 bool is_generic_wasm_to_js =
2054 code->is_builtin() && code->builtin_id() == Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA;
2055 bool is_optimized_wasm_to_js = this->type() == WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION;
2056 if (is_generic_wasm_to_js) {
2057 IterateParamsOfGenericWasmToJSWrapper(v);
2058 } else if (is_optimized_wasm_to_js) {
2059 IterateParamsOfOptimizedWasmToJSWrapper(v);
2060 }
2061#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2062 DCHECK(code->is_turbofanned());
2063 SafepointEntry safepoint_entry =
2064 GetSafepointEntryFromCodeCache(isolate(), inner_pointer, entry);
2065
2066#ifdef DEBUG
2067 intptr_t marker =
2068 Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
2069 DCHECK(StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
2070#endif // DEBUG
2071
2072 // Determine the fixed header and spill slot area size.
2073 int frame_header_size = TypedFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
2074 int spill_slots_size =
2075 code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize -
2076 (frame_header_size + StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp);
2077
2078 // Fixed frame slots.
2079 FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() - frame_header_size));
2080 FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
2081 &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
2082 // Parameters passed to the callee.
2083#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2084 // Frame layout without stack switching (stack grows upwards):
2085 //
2086 // | callee |
2087 // | frame |
2088 // |-------------| <- sp()
2089 // | out params |
2090 // |-------------| <- frame_header_base - spill_slot_space
2091 // | spill slots |
2092 // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
2093 // | frame header|
2094 // |-------------| <- fp()
2095 //
2096 // With stack-switching:
2097 //
2098 // Secondary stack: Central stack:
2099 //
2100 // | callee |
2101 // | frame |
2102 // |------------| <- sp()
2103 // | out params |
2104 // |-------------| |------------| <- maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
2105 // | spill slots |
2106 // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
2107 // | frame header|
2108 // |-------------| <- fp()
2109 //
2110 // The base (lowest address) of the outgoing stack parameters area is always
2111 // sp(), and the limit (highest address) is either {frame_header_base -
2112 // spill_slot_size} or {maybe_stack_switch.target_sp} depending on
2113 // stack-switching.
2114 wasm::StackMemory::StackSwitchInfo maybe_stack_switch;
2115 if (iterator_->wasm_stack() != nullptr) {
2116 maybe_stack_switch = iterator_->wasm_stack()->stack_switch_info();
2117 }
2118 FullObjectSlot parameters_limit(
2119 maybe_stack_switch.has_value() && maybe_stack_switch.source_fp == fp()
2120 ? maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
2121 : frame_header_base.address() - spill_slots_size);
2122#else
2123 FullObjectSlot parameters_limit(frame_header_base.address() -
2124 spill_slots_size);
2125#endif
2126 FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
2127 FullObjectSlot spill_slots_end(frame_header_base.address() -
2128 spill_slots_size);
2129
2130 // Visit the rest of the parameters.
2131 if (HasTaggedOutgoingParams(code)) {
2132 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
2133 parameters_limit);
2134 }
2135
2136 // Visit pointer spill slots and locals.
2137 DCHECK_GE((code->stack_slots() + kBitsPerByte) / kBitsPerByte,
2138 safepoint_entry.tagged_slots().size());
2139 VisitSpillSlots(isolate(), v, spill_slots_end,
2140 safepoint_entry.tagged_slots());
2141
2142 // Visit fixed header region.
2143 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base,
2144 frame_header_limit);
2145
2146 // Visit the return address in the callee and incoming arguments.
2147 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
2148}
2149
2150void MaglevFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
2151 DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
2152
2153 // === MaglevFrame ===
2154 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2155 // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
2156 // | ... |
2157 // | out_param 0 |
2158 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2159 // | pushed_double n | <-- parameters_limit ^
2160 // | ... | |
2161 // | pushed_double 0 | |
2162 // +- - - - - - - - -+ num_extra_spill_slots
2163 // | pushed_reg n | |
2164 // | ... | |
2165 // | pushed_reg 0 | <-- pushed_register_base v
2166 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2167 // | untagged_slot n | ^
2168 // | ... | |
2169 // | untagged_slot 0 | |
2170 // +- - - - - - - - -+ spill_slot_count
2171 // | tagged_slot n | |
2172 // | ... | |
2173 // | tagged_slot 0 | v
2174 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2175 // | argc | <-- frame_header_base ^
2176 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2177 // | JSFunction | |
2178 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2179 // | Context | |
2180 // |- - - - - - - - -| kFixedSlotCount
2181 // | [Constant Pool] | |
2182 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2183 // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
2184 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2185 // | return addr | v
2186 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2187
2188 // Find the code and compute the safepoint information.
2189 Address inner_pointer = pc();
2190 InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
2191 isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(inner_pointer);
2192 CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
2193 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
2194 DCHECK(code->is_maglevved());
2195 MaglevSafepointEntry maglev_safepoint_entry =
2196 GetMaglevSafepointEntryFromCodeCache(isolate(), inner_pointer, entry);
2197
2198#ifdef DEBUG
2199 // Assert that it is a JS frame and it has a context.
2200 intptr_t marker =
2201 Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
2202 DCHECK(!StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
2203#endif // DEBUG
2204
2205 // Fixed frame slots.
2206 FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(
2207 &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp));
2208 FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
2209 &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
2210
2211 // Determine spill slot area count.
2212 uint32_t tagged_slot_count = maglev_safepoint_entry.num_tagged_slots();
2213 uint32_t spill_slot_count =
2214 code->stack_slots() - StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCount;
2215
2216 // Visit the outgoing parameters if they are tagged.
2217 DCHECK(code->has_tagged_outgoing_params());
2218 FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
2219 FullObjectSlot parameters_limit =
2220 frame_header_base - spill_slot_count -
2221 maglev_safepoint_entry.num_extra_spill_slots();
2222 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
2223 parameters_limit);
2224
2225 // Maglev can also spill registers, tagged and untagged, just before making
2226 // a call. These are distinct from normal spill slots and live between the
2227 // normal spill slots and the pushed parameters. Some of these are tagged,
2228 // as indicated by the tagged register indexes, and should be visited too.
2229 if (maglev_safepoint_entry.num_extra_spill_slots() > 0) {
2230 FullObjectSlot pushed_register_base =
2231 frame_header_base - spill_slot_count - 1;
2232 uint32_t tagged_register_indexes =
2233 maglev_safepoint_entry.tagged_register_indexes();
2234 while (tagged_register_indexes != 0) {
2235 int index = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(tagged_register_indexes);
2236 tagged_register_indexes &= ~(1 << index);
2237 FullObjectSlot spill_slot = pushed_register_base - index;
2238 VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, spill_slot);
2239 }
2240 }
2241
2242 // Visit tagged spill slots.
2243 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < tagged_slot_count; ++i) {
2244 FullObjectSlot spill_slot = frame_header_base - 1 - i;
2245 VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, spill_slot);
2246 }
2247
2248 // Visit fixed header region (the context and JSFunction), skipping the
2249 // argument count since it is stored untagged.
2250 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base + 1,
2251 frame_header_limit);
2252
2253 // Visit the return address in the callee and incoming arguments.
2254 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
2255}

2257Handle<JSFunction> MaglevFrame::GetInnermostFunction() const {
2258 return Summarize().frames.back().AsJavaScript().function();
2259}
2260
2261BytecodeOffset MaglevFrame::GetBytecodeOffsetForOSR() const {
2262 int deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
2263 Tagged<Code> code = LookupCode();
2264 const Tagged<DeoptimizationData> data =
2265 GetDeoptimizationData(code, &deopt_index);
2266 if (deopt_index == SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex) {
2267 CHECK(data.is_null());
2268 FATAL(
2269 "Missing deoptimization information for OptimizedJSFrame::Summarize.");
2270 }
2271
2272 DeoptimizationFrameTranslation::Iterator it(
2273 data->FrameTranslation(), data->TranslationIndex(deopt_index).value());
2274 // Search the innermost interpreter frame and get its bailout id. The
2275 // translation stores frames bottom up.
2276 int js_frames = it.EnterBeginOpcode().js_frame_count;
2277 DCHECK_GT(js_frames, 0);
2278 BytecodeOffset offset = BytecodeOffset::None();
2279 while (js_frames > 0) {
2280 TranslationOpcode frame = it.SeekNextJSFrame();
2281 --js_frames;
2282 if (IsTranslationInterpreterFrameOpcode(frame)) {
2283 offset = BytecodeOffset(it.NextOperand());
2284 it.SkipOperands(TranslationOpcodeOperandCount(frame) - 1);
2285 } else {
2286 it.SkipOperands(TranslationOpcodeOperandCount(frame));
2287 }
2288 }
2289
2290 return offset;
2291}
2292
2293bool CommonFrame::HasTaggedOutgoingParams(
2294 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code_lookup) const {
2295#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2296 // With inlined JS-to-Wasm calls, we can be in an OptimizedJSFrame and
2297 // directly call a Wasm function from JavaScript. In this case the Wasm frame
2298 // is responsible for visiting incoming potentially tagged parameters.
2299 // (This is required for tail-call support: If the direct callee tail-called
2300 // another function which then caused a GC, the caller would not be able to
2301 // determine where there might be tagged parameters.)
2302 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_callee =
2303 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), callee_pc());
2304 if (wasm_callee) return false;
2305
2306 Tagged<Code> wrapper =
2307 isolate()->builtins()->code(Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA);
2308 if (callee_pc() >= wrapper->instruction_start() &&
2309 callee_pc() <= wrapper->instruction_end()) {
2310 return false;
2311 }
2312 return code_lookup->has_tagged_outgoing_params();
2313#else
2314 return code_lookup->has_tagged_outgoing_params();
2315#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2316}

2325void CommonFrame::IterateTurbofanJSOptimizedFrame(RootVisitor* v) const {
2326 DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
2327
2328 // === TurbofanJSFrame ===
2329 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2330 // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
2331 // | ... |
2332 // | out_param 0 |
2333 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2334 // | spill_slot n | <-- parameters_limit ^
2335 // | ... | spill_slot_count
2336 // | spill_slot 0 | v
2337 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2338 // | argc | <-- frame_header_base ^
2339 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2340 // | JSFunction | |
2341 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2342 // | Context | |
2343 // |- - - - - - - - -| kFixedSlotCount
2344 // | [Constant Pool] | |
2345 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2346 // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
2347 // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2348 // | return addr | v
2349 // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2350
2351 // Find the code and compute the safepoint information.
2352 const Address inner_pointer = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
2353 InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
2354 isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(inner_pointer);
2355 CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
2356 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
2357 DCHECK(code->is_turbofanned());
2358 SafepointEntry safepoint_entry =
2359 GetSafepointEntryFromCodeCache(isolate(), inner_pointer, entry);
2360
2361#ifdef DEBUG
2362 // Assert that it is a JS frame and it has a context.
2363 intptr_t marker =
2364 Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
2365 DCHECK(!StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
2366#endif // DEBUG
2367
2368 // Determine the fixed header and spill slot area size.
2369 int frame_header_size = StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
2370 int spill_slot_count =
2371 code->stack_slots() - StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCount;
2372
2373 // Fixed frame slots.
2374 FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() - frame_header_size));
2375 FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
2376 &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
2377
2378 FullObjectSlot parameters_limit = frame_header_base - spill_slot_count;
2379
2380 if (!InFastCCall()) {
2381 // Parameters passed to the callee.
2382 FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
2383
2384 // Visit the outgoing parameters if they are tagged.
2385 if (HasTaggedOutgoingParams(code)) {
2386 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
2387 parameters_limit);
2388 }
2389 } else {
2390 // There are no outgoing parameters to visit for fast C calls.
2391 }
2392
2393 // Spill slots are in the region ]frame_header_base, parameters_limit];
2394 // Visit pointer spill slots and locals.
2395 DCHECK_GE((code->stack_slots() + kBitsPerByte) / kBitsPerByte,
2396 safepoint_entry.tagged_slots().size());
2397 VisitSpillSlots(isolate(), v, parameters_limit,
2398 safepoint_entry.tagged_slots());
2399
2400 // Visit fixed header region (the context and JSFunction), skipping the
2401 // argument count since it is stored untagged.
2402 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base + 1,
2403 frame_header_limit);
2404
2405 // Visit the return address in the callee and incoming arguments.
2406 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
2407}

2413void TurbofanJSFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {

2417Tagged<HeapObject> StubFrame::unchecked_code() const {
2418 std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> code_lookup =
2419 isolate()->heap()->GcSafeTryFindCodeForInnerPointer(pc());
2420 if (!code_lookup.has_value()) return {};
2421 return code_lookup.value();
2422}
2423
2424int StubFrame::LookupExceptionHandlerInTable() {
2425 Tagged<Code> code;
2426 int pc_offset = -1;
2427 std::tie(code, pc_offset) = LookupCodeAndOffset();
2428 DCHECK(code->is_turbofanned());
2429 DCHECK(code->has_handler_table());
2430 HandlerTable table(code);
2431 return table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
2432}
2433
2434FrameSummaries StubFrame::Summarize() const {
2435 FrameSummaries summaries;
2436#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2437 Tagged<Code> code = LookupCode();
2438 if (code->kind() != CodeKind::BUILTIN) return summaries;
2439 // We skip most stub frames from stack traces, but a few builtins
2440 // specifically exist to pretend to be another builtin throwing an
2441 // exception.
2442 switch (code->builtin_id()) {
2443 case Builtin::kThrowDataViewTypeError:
2444 case Builtin::kThrowDataViewDetachedError:
2445 case Builtin::kThrowDataViewOutOfBounds:
2446 case Builtin::kThrowIndexOfCalledOnNull:
2447 case Builtin::kThrowToLowerCaseCalledOnNull:
2448 case Builtin::kWasmIntToString: {
2449 // When adding builtins here, also implement naming support for them.
2450 DCHECK_NE(nullptr,
2451 Builtins::NameForStackTrace(isolate(), code->builtin_id()));
2452 FrameSummary::BuiltinFrameSummary summary(isolate(), code->builtin_id());
2453 summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
2454 break;
2455 }
2456 default:
2457 break;
2458 }
2459#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2460 return summaries;
2461}

2506std::tuple<Tagged<AbstractCode>, int> JavaScriptFrame::GetActiveCodeAndOffset()
2507 const {
2508 int code_offset = 0;
2509 Tagged<AbstractCode> abstract_code;
2510 if (is_interpreted()) {
2511 const InterpretedFrame* iframe = InterpretedFrame::cast(this);
2512 code_offset = iframe->GetBytecodeOffset();
2513 abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(iframe->GetBytecodeArray());
2514 } else if (is_baseline()) {
2515 // TODO(pthier): AbstractCode should fully support Baseline code.
2516 const BaselineFrame* baseline_frame = BaselineFrame::cast(this);
2517 code_offset = baseline_frame->GetBytecodeOffset();
2518 abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(baseline_frame->GetBytecodeArray());
2519 } else {
2520 Tagged<Code> code;
2521 int pc_offset = -1;
2522 std::tie(code, pc_offset) = LookupCodeAndOffset();
2523 abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(code);
2524 }
2525 return {abstract_code, code_offset};
2526}

2584
2585void JavaScriptFrame::PrintFunctionAndOffset(Isolate* isolate,
2586 Tagged<JSFunction> function,
2587 Tagged<AbstractCode> code,
2588 int code_offset, FILE* file,
2589 bool print_line_number) {
2590 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(function);
2591 PrintF(file, "%s", CodeKindToMarker(code->kind(cage_base), false));
2592 function->PrintName(file);
2593 PrintF(file, "+%d", code_offset);
2594 if (print_line_number) {
2595 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared();
2596 int source_pos = code->SourcePosition(isolate, code_offset);
2597 Tagged<Object> maybe_script = shared->script();
2598 if (IsScript(maybe_script)) {
2599 Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(maybe_script);
2600 int line = script->GetLineNumber(source_pos) + 1;
2601 Tagged<Object> script_name_raw = script->name();
2602 if (IsString(script_name_raw)) {
2603 Tagged<String> script_name = Cast<String>(script->name());
2604 std::unique_ptr<char[]> c_script_name = script_name->ToCString();
2605 PrintF(file, " at %s:%d", c_script_name.get(), line);
2606 } else {
2607 PrintF(file, " at <unknown>:%d", line);
2608 }
2609 } else {
2610 PrintF(file, " at <unknown>:<unknown>");
2611 }
2612 }
2613}
2614
2615void JavaScriptFrame::PrintTop(Isolate* isolate, FILE* file, bool print_args,
2616 bool print_line_number) {
2617 // constructor calls
2618 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2619 JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(isolate);
2620 while (!it.done()) {
2621 if (it.frame()->is_javascript()) {
2622 JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
2623 if (frame->IsConstructor()) PrintF(file, "new ");
2624 Tagged<JSFunction> function = frame->function();
2625 int code_offset = 0;
2626 Tagged<AbstractCode> code;
2627 std::tie(code, code_offset) = frame->GetActiveCodeAndOffset();
2628 PrintFunctionAndOffset(isolate, function, code, code_offset, file,
2629 print_line_number);
2630 if (print_args) {
2631 // function arguments
2632 // (we are intentionally only printing the actually
2633 // supplied parameters, not all parameters required)
2634 PrintF(file, "(this=");
2635 ShortPrint(frame->receiver(), file);
2636 const int length = frame->ComputeParametersCount();
2637 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2638 PrintF(file, ", ");
2639 ShortPrint(frame->GetParameter(i), file);
2640 }
2641 PrintF(file, ")");
2642 }
2643 break;
2644 }
2645 it.Advance();
2646 }
2647}

2649// static
2650void JavaScriptFrame::CollectFunctionAndOffsetForICStats(
2651 Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSFunction> function, Tagged<AbstractCode> code,
2652 int code_offset) {
2653 auto ic_stats = ICStats::instance();
2654 ICInfo& ic_info = ic_stats->Current();
2655 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(function);
2656 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared(cage_base);
2657
2658 ic_info.function_name = ic_stats->GetOrCacheFunctionName(isolate, function);
2659 ic_info.script_offset = code_offset;
2660
2661 int source_pos = code->SourcePosition(isolate, code_offset);
2662 Tagged<Object> maybe_script = shared->script(cage_base, kAcquireLoad);
2663 if (IsScript(maybe_script, cage_base)) {
2664 Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(maybe_script);
2665 Script::PositionInfo info;
2666 script->GetPositionInfo(source_pos, &info);
2667 ic_info.line_num = info.line + 1;
2668 ic_info.column_num = info.column + 1;
2669 ic_info.script_name = ic_stats->GetOrCacheScriptName(script);
2670 }
2671}

2810Handle<StackFrameInfo>
2811FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary::CreateStackFrameInfo() const {
2812 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function_->shared(), isolate());
2813 DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate());
2814 DirectHandle<String> function_name = JSFunction::GetDebugName(function_);
2815 if (function_name->length() == 0 &&
2816 script->compilation_type() == Script::CompilationType::kEval) {
2817 function_name = isolate()->factory()->eval_string();
2818 }
2819 int bytecode_offset = code_offset();
2820 if (bytecode_offset == kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset) {
2821 // For the special function entry bytecode offset (-1), which signals
2822 // that the stack trace was captured while the function entry was
2823 // executing (i.e. during the interrupt check), we cannot store this
2824 // sentinel in the bit field, so we just eagerly lookup the source
2825 // position within the script.
2826 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate(), shared);
2827 int source_position =
2828 abstract_code()->SourcePosition(isolate(), bytecode_offset);
2829 return isolate()->factory()->NewStackFrameInfo(
2830 script, source_position, function_name, is_constructor());
2831 }
2832 return isolate()->factory()->NewStackFrameInfo(
2833 shared, bytecode_offset, function_name, is_constructor());
2834}
