3081FrameSummaries OptimizedJSFrame::Summarize() const {
3082 DCHECK(is_optimized());
3083 FrameSummaries summaries;
3084
3085 // Delegate to JS frame in absence of deoptimization info.
3086 // TODO(turbofan): Revisit once we support deoptimization across the board.
3087 DirectHandle<Code> code(LookupCode(), isolate());
3088 if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BUILTIN) {
3089 return JavaScriptFrame::Summarize();
3090 }
3091
3092 int deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
3093 Tagged<DeoptimizationData> const data =
3094 GetDeoptimizationData(*code, &deopt_index);
3095 if (deopt_index == SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex) {
3096 // Hack: For maglevved function entry, we don't emit lazy deopt information,
3097 // so create an extra special summary here.
3098 //
3099 // TODO(leszeks): Remove this hack, by having a maglev-specific frame
3100 // summary which is a bit more aware of maglev behaviour and can e.g. handle
3101 // more compact safepointed frame information for both function entry and
3102 // loop stack checks.
3103 if (code->is_maglevved()) {
3104 DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code(
3105 Cast<AbstractCode>(function()->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate())),
3106 isolate());
3107 DirectHandle<FixedArray> params = GetParameters();
3108 FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary summary(
3109 isolate(), receiver(), function(), *abstract_code,
3110 kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset, IsConstructor(), *params);
3111 summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3112 return summaries;
3113 }
3114
3115 CHECK(data.is_null());
3116 FATAL(
3117 "Missing deoptimization information for OptimizedJSFrame::Summarize.");
3118 }
3119
3120 // Prepare iteration over translation. We must not materialize values here
3121 // because we do not deoptimize the function.
3122 TranslatedState translated(this);
3123 translated.Prepare(fp());
3124
3125 // We create the summary in reverse order because the frames
3126 // in the deoptimization translation are ordered bottom-to-top.
3127 bool is_constructor = IsConstructor();
3128 for (auto it = translated.begin(); it != translated.end(); it++) {
3129 if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kUnoptimizedFunction ||
3130 it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation ||
3131 it->kind() ==
3132 TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatch) {
3133 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = it->shared_info();
3134
3135 // The translation commands are ordered and the function is always
3136 // at the first position, and the receiver is next.
3137 TranslatedFrame::iterator translated_values = it->begin();
3138
3139 // Get the correct function in the optimized frame.
3140 CHECK(!translated_values->IsMaterializedObject());
3141 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function =
3142 Cast<JSFunction>(translated_values->GetValue());
3143 translated_values++;
3144
3145 // Get the correct receiver in the optimized frame.
3146 CHECK(!translated_values->IsMaterializedObject());
3147 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = translated_values->GetValue();
3148 translated_values++;
3149
3150 // Determine the underlying code object and the position within it from
3151 // the translation corresponding to the frame type in question.
3152 DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code;
3153 unsigned code_offset;
3154 if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation ||
3155 it->kind() ==
3156 TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatch) {
3157 code_offset = 0;
3158 abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(
3159 Builtins::GetBuiltinFromBytecodeOffset(it->bytecode_offset())));
3160 } else {
3161 DCHECK_EQ(it->kind(), TranslatedFrame::kUnoptimizedFunction);
3162 code_offset = it->bytecode_offset().ToInt();
3163 abstract_code =
3164 direct_handle(shared_info->abstract_code(isolate()), isolate());
3165 }
3166
3167 // Append full summary of the encountered JS frame.
3168 DirectHandle<FixedArray> params = GetParameters();
3169 FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary summary(
3170 isolate(), *receiver, *function, *abstract_code, code_offset,
3171 is_constructor, *params);
3172 summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3173 is_constructor = false;
3174 } else if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kConstructCreateStub ||
3175 it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kConstructInvokeStub) {
3176 // The next encountered JS frame will be marked as a constructor call.
3177 DCHECK(!is_constructor);
3178 is_constructor = true;
3179#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3180 } else if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kWasmInlinedIntoJS) {
3181 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = it->shared_info();
3182 DCHECK_NE(isolate()->heap()->gc_state(), Heap::MARK_COMPACT);
3183
3184 Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> function_data =
3185 shared_info->wasm_exported_function_data();
3186 Handle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance{function_data->instance_data(),
3187 isolate()};
3188 int func_index = function_data->function_index();
3189 FrameSummary::WasmInlinedFrameSummary summary(
3190 isolate(), instance, func_index, it->bytecode_offset().ToInt());
3191 summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3192#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3193 }
3194 }
3195 if (is_constructor) {
3196 // If {is_constructor} is true, then we haven't inlined the contructor in
3197 // the optimized frames and the previous visited frame (top of the inlined
3198 // frames) is a construct call.
3199 summaries.top_frame_is_construct_call = true;
3200 }
3201 return summaries;
3202}
3203
3204int OptimizedJSFrame::LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(
3205 int* data, HandlerTable::CatchPrediction* prediction) {
3206 // We cannot perform exception prediction on optimized code. Instead, we need
3207 // to use FrameSummary to find the corresponding code offset in unoptimized
3208 // code to perform prediction there.
3209 DCHECK_NULL(prediction);
3210 Tagged<Code> code;
3211 int pc_offset = -1;
3212 std::tie(code, pc_offset) = LookupCodeAndOffset();
3213
3214 HandlerTable table(code);
3215 if (table.NumberOfReturnEntries() == 0) return -1;
3216
3217 DCHECK_NULL(data); // Data is not used and will not return a value.
3218
3219 // When the return pc has been replaced by a trampoline there won't be
3220 // a handler for this trampoline. Thus we need to use the return pc that
3221 // _used to be_ on the stack to get the right ExceptionHandler.
3222 if (CodeKindCanDeoptimize(code->kind())) {
3223 if (!code->marked_for_deoptimization()) {
3224 // Lazy deoptimize the function in case the handler table entry flags that
3225 // it wants to be lazily deoptimized on throw. This allows the optimizing
3226 // compiler to omit catch blocks that were never reached in practice.
3227 int optimized_exception_handler = table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
3228 if (optimized_exception_handler != HandlerTable::kLazyDeopt) {
3229 return optimized_exception_handler;
3230 }
3231 Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeFunction(
3232 function(), LazyDeoptimizeReason::kExceptionCaught, code);
3233 }
3234 DCHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
3235 pc_offset = FindReturnPCForTrampoline(code, pc_offset);
3236 }
3237 return table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
3238}
3239

3241 int trampoline_pc) const {
3242 DCHECK_EQ(code->kind(), CodeKind::MAGLEV);
3243 DCHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
3244 MaglevSafepointTable safepoints(isolate(), pc(), code);

3248int TurbofanJSFrame::FindReturnPCForTrampoline(Tagged<Code> code,

3250 DCHECK_EQ(code->kind(), CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
3251 DCHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());

3256Tagged<DeoptimizationData> OptimizedJSFrame::GetDeoptimizationData(
3257 Tagged<Code> code, int* deopt_index) const {
3258 DCHECK(is_optimized());
3259
3260 Address pc = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
3261
3262 DCHECK(code->contains(isolate(), pc));
3263 DCHECK(CodeKindCanDeoptimize(code->kind()));
3264
3265 if (code->is_maglevved()) {
3266 MaglevSafepointEntry safepoint_entry =
3267 code->GetMaglevSafepointEntry(isolate(), pc);
3268 if (safepoint_entry.has_deoptimization_index()) {
3269 *deopt_index = safepoint_entry.deoptimization_index();
3270 return Cast<DeoptimizationData>(code->deoptimization_data());
3271 }
3272 } else {
3273 SafepointEntry safepoint_entry = code->GetSafepointEntry(isolate(), pc);
3274 if (safepoint_entry.has_deoptimization_index()) {
3275 *deopt_index = safepoint_entry.deoptimization_index();
3276 return Cast<DeoptimizationData>(code->deoptimization_data());
3277 }
3278 }
3279 *deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
3280 return {};
3281}

3283void OptimizedJSFrame::GetFunctions(
3284 std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>>* functions) const {
3285 DCHECK(functions->empty());
3286 DCHECK(is_optimized());
3287
3288 // Delegate to JS frame in absence of turbofan deoptimization.
3289 // TODO(turbofan): Revisit once we support deoptimization across the board.
3290 Tagged<Code> code = LookupCode();
3291 if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BUILTIN) {
3292 return JavaScriptFrame::GetFunctions(functions);
3293 }
3294
3295 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3296 int deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
3297 Tagged<DeoptimizationData> const data =
3298 GetDeoptimizationData(code, &deopt_index);
3299 DCHECK(!data.is_null());
3300 DCHECK_NE(SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex, deopt_index);
3301 Tagged<DeoptimizationLiteralArray> const literal_array = data->LiteralArray();
3302
3303 DeoptimizationFrameTranslation::Iterator it(
3304 data->FrameTranslation(), data->TranslationIndex(deopt_index).value());
3305 int jsframe_count = it.EnterBeginOpcode().js_frame_count;
3306
3307 // We insert the frames in reverse order because the frames
3308 // in the deoptimization translation are ordered bottom-to-top.
3309 while (jsframe_count != 0) {
3310 TranslationOpcode opcode = it.SeekNextJSFrame();
3311 it.NextOperand(); // Skip bailout id.
3312 jsframe_count--;
3313
3314 // The second operand of the frame points to the function.
3315 Tagged<Object> shared = literal_array->get(it.NextOperand());
3316 functions->push_back(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(shared));
3317
3318 // Skip over remaining operands to advance to the next opcode.
3319 it.SkipOperands(TranslationOpcodeOperandCount(opcode) - 2);
3320 }
3321}

3516
3517FrameSummaries WasmFrame::Summarize() const {
3518 FrameSummaries summaries;
3519 // The {WasmCode*} escapes this scope via the {FrameSummary}, which is fine,
3520 // since this code object is part of our stack.
3521 wasm::WasmCode* code = wasm_code();
3522 int offset =
3523 static_cast<int>(maybe_unauthenticated_pc() - code->instruction_start());
3524 Handle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data{trusted_instance_data(),
3525 isolate()};
3526 // Push regular non-inlined summary.
3527 SourcePosition pos = code->GetSourcePositionBefore(offset);
3528 bool at_conversion = at_to_number_conversion();
3529 bool child_was_tail_call = false;
3530 // Add summaries for each inlined function at the current location.
3531 while (pos.isInlined()) {
3532 // Use current pc offset as the code offset for inlined functions.
3533 // This is not fully correct but there isn't a real code offset of a stack
3534 // frame for an inlined function as the inlined function is not a true
3535 // function with a defined start and end in the generated code.
3536 const auto [func_index, was_tail_call, caller_pos] =
3537 code->GetInliningPosition(pos.InliningId());
3538 if (!child_was_tail_call) {
3539 FrameSummary::WasmFrameSummary summary(isolate(), instance_data, code,
3540 pos.ScriptOffset(), func_index,
3541 at_conversion);
3542 summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3543 }
3544 pos = caller_pos;
3545 at_conversion = false;
3546 child_was_tail_call = was_tail_call;
3547 }
3548
3549 if (!child_was_tail_call) {
3550 int func_index = code->index();
3551 FrameSummary::WasmFrameSummary summary(isolate(), instance_data, code,
3552 pos.ScriptOffset(), func_index,
3553 at_conversion);
3554 summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3555 }
3556
3557 // The caller has to be on top.
3558 std::reverse(summaries.frames.begin(), summaries.frames.end());
3559 return summaries;
3560}
3561
3562bool WasmFrame::at_to_number_conversion() const {
3563 if (callee_pc() == kNullAddress) return false;
3564 // Check whether our callee is a WASM_TO_JS frame, and this frame is at the
3565 // ToNumber conversion call.
3566 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code =
3567 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), callee_pc());
3568
3569 if (wasm_code) {
3570 if (wasm_code->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper) return false;
3571 int offset = static_cast<int>(callee_pc() - wasm_code->instruction_start());
3572 int pos = wasm_code->GetSourceOffsetBefore(offset);
3573 // The imported call has position 0, ToNumber has position 1.
3574 // If there is no source position available, this is also not a ToNumber
3575 // call.
3576 DCHECK(pos == wasm::kNoCodePosition || pos == 0 || pos == 1);
3577 return pos == 1;
3578 }
3579
3580 InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
3581 isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(callee_pc());
3582 CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
3583 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
3584 if (code->builtin_id() != Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA) {
3585 return false;
3586 }
3587
3588 // The generic wasm-to-js wrapper maintains a slot on the stack to indicate
3589 // its state. Initially this slot contains a pointer to the signature, so that
3590 // incoming parameters can be scanned. After all parameters have been
3591 // processed, this slot is reset to nullptr. After returning from JavaScript,
3592 // -1 is stored in the slot to indicate that any call from now on is a
3593 // ToNumber conversion.
3594 Address maybe_sig =
3595 Memory<Address>(callee_fp() + WasmToJSWrapperConstants::kSignatureOffset);
3596
3597 return static_cast<intptr_t>(maybe_sig) == -1;
3598}
3599
3600int WasmFrame::LookupExceptionHandlerInTable() {
3601 wasm::WasmCode* code =
3602 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), pc());
3603 if (!code->IsAnonymous() && code->handler_table_size() > 0) {
3604 HandlerTable table(code);
3605 int pc_offset = static_cast<int>(pc() - code->instruction_start());
3606 return table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
3607 }
3608 return -1;
3609}
3610
3611void WasmDebugBreakFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3612 DCHECK(caller_pc());
3613 auto pair = wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCodeAndSafepoint(isolate(),
3614 caller_pc());
3615 SafepointEntry safepoint_entry = pair.second;
3616 uint32_t tagged_register_indexes = safepoint_entry.tagged_register_indexes();
3617
3618 while (tagged_register_indexes != 0) {
3619 int reg_code = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(tagged_register_indexes);
3620 tagged_register_indexes &= ~(1 << reg_code);
3621 FullObjectSlot spill_slot(&Memory<Address>(
3622 fp() +
3623 WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::GetPushedGpRegisterOffset(reg_code)));
3624
3625 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot);
3626 }
3627}

3649
3650void JsToWasmFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3651 // WrapperBuffer slot is RawPtr pointing to a stack.
3652 // Wasm instance and JS result array are passed as stack params.
3653 // So there is no need to visit them.
3654
3655#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3656 // Please reference GenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper for stack layout.
3657 if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
3658 DCHECK(GetContainingCode(isolate(), pc()).value()->builtin_id() ==
3659 Builtin::kGenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper);
3660
3661 // In a GenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper stack layout
3662 // ------+-----------------+----------------------
3663 // | return addr |
3664 // fp |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3665 // | old fp | |
3666 // fp-p |- - - - - - - - -| |
3667 // | frame marker | | no GC scan
3668 // fp-2p |- - - - - - - - -| |
3669 // | scan_count | |
3670 // fp-3p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3671 // | .... | |
3672 // | .... | <- spill_slot_limit |
3673 // | spill slots | | GC scan scan_count slots
3674 // sp | .... | <- spill_slot_base--|
3675 // | | |
3676 // The [fp + BuiltinFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCount] on the stack is a
3677 // value indicating how many values should be scanned from the top.
3678 intptr_t scan_count = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3679 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3680
3681 FullObjectSlot spill_slot_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
3682 FullObjectSlot spill_slot_limit(
3683 &Memory<Address>(sp() + scan_count * kSystemPointerSize));
3684 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot_base,
3685 spill_slot_limit);
3686
3687 // We should scan the arg/return values array which may hold heap pointers
3688 // for reference type of parameter/return values.
3689 uint32_t signature_data = *reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(
3690 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kSignatureDataOffset);
3691 bool has_ref_args =
3692 signature_data & wasm::WasmInterpreterRuntime::HasRefArgsField::kMask;
3693 bool has_ref_rets =
3694 signature_data & wasm::WasmInterpreterRuntime::HasRefRetsField::kMask;
3695
3696 // This value indicates the array is currently used as args array. If false,
3697 // it's an array for return values.
3698 bool is_args = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3699 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kArgRetsIsArgsOffset);
3700 if ((is_args && !has_ref_args) || (!is_args && !has_ref_rets)) return;
3701
3702 // Retrieve function signature.
3703 size_t return_count = *reinterpret_cast<size_t*>(
3704 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kReturnCountOffset);
3705 size_t param_count = *reinterpret_cast<size_t*>(
3706 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kParamCountOffset);
3707 const wasm::ValueType* reps = *reinterpret_cast<const wasm::ValueType**>(
3708 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kSigRepsOffset);
3709 wasm::FunctionSig sig(return_count, param_count, reps);
3710
3711 intptr_t slot_ptr = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3712 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kArgRetsAddressOffset);
3713
3714 if (is_args) {
3715 size_t current_index = *reinterpret_cast<size_t*>(
3716 fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kCurrentIndexOffset);
3717 DCHECK_LE(current_index, param_count);
3718 for (size_t i = 0; i < current_index; i++) {
3719 wasm::ValueType type = sig.GetParam(i);
3720 if (type.is_reference()) {
3721 // Make sure slot for ref args are 64-bit aligned.
3722 slot_ptr += (slot_ptr & 0x04); // Branchless.
3723 FullObjectSlot array_slot(&Memory<Address>(slot_ptr));
3724 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, array_slot);
3725 slot_ptr += kSystemPointerSize;
3726 } else {
3727 switch (type.kind()) {
3728 case wasm::kI32:
3729 case wasm::kF32:
3730 slot_ptr += sizeof(int32_t);
3731 break;
3732 case wasm::kI64:
3733 case wasm::kF64:
3734 slot_ptr += sizeof(int64_t);
3735 break;
3736 case wasm::kS128:
3737 default:
3738 UNREACHABLE();
3739 }
3740 }
3741 }
3742 } else {
3743 // When converting return values, all results are already in the array.
3744 for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
3745 wasm::ValueType type = sig.GetReturn(i);
3746 if (type.is_reference()) {
3747 // Make sure slot for ref args are 64-bit aligned.
3748 slot_ptr += (slot_ptr & 0x04); // Branchless.
3749 FullObjectSlot array_slot(&Memory<Address>(slot_ptr));
3750 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, array_slot);
3751 slot_ptr += kSystemPointerSize;
3752 } else {
3753 switch (type.kind()) {
3754 case wasm::kI32:
3755 case wasm::kF32:
3756 slot_ptr += sizeof(int32_t);
3757 break;
3758 case wasm::kI64:
3759 case wasm::kF64:
3760 slot_ptr += sizeof(int64_t);
3761 break;
3762 case wasm::kS128:
3763 default:
3764 UNREACHABLE();
3765 }
3766 }
3767 }
3768 }
3769 }
3770#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3771}

3777 CHECK(v8_flags.jitless);
3778 // The [fp + BuiltinFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotLimit] on the stack is a
3779 // pointer to the end of the stack frame area that contains tagged objects.

3793void StackSwitchFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3794 // See JsToWasmFrame layout.
3795 // We cannot DCHECK that the pc matches the expected builtin code here,
3796 // because the return address is on a different stack.
3797 // The [fp + BuiltinFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset] on the stack is a
3798 // value indicating how many values should be scanned from the top.
3799 intptr_t scan_count = Memory<intptr_t>(
3800 fp() + StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3801
3802 FullObjectSlot spill_slot_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
3803 FullObjectSlot spill_slot_limit(
3804 &Memory<Address>(sp() + scan_count * kSystemPointerSize));
3805 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot_base,
3806 spill_slot_limit);
3807 // Also visit fixed spill slots that contain references.
3808 FullObjectSlot instance_slot(
3809 &Memory<Address>(fp() + StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
3810 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, instance_slot);
3811 FullObjectSlot result_array_slot(
3812 &Memory<Address>(fp() + StackSwitchFrameConstants::kResultArrayOffset));
3813 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, result_array_slot);
3814}

3817void WasmInterpreterEntryFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3818 // WasmInterpreterEntryFrame stack layout
3819 // ------+-----------------+----------------------
3820 // | return addr | |
3821 // fp |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3822 // | prev fp | |
3823 // fp-p |- - - - - - - - -| | no GC scan
3824 // | frame marker | |
3825 // fp-2p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|-------------
3826 // | WasmInstanceObj | | GC scan
3827 // fp-3p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|-------------
3828 // | function_index | |
3829 // fp-4p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------| no GC scan
3830 // | array_start | |
3831 // fp-5p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|

3833 static constexpr int kWasmInstanceObjOffset = -2 * kSystemPointerSize;
3834 FullObjectSlot slot_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() + kWasmInstanceObjOffset));
3835 FullObjectSlot slot_limit(
3836 &Memory<Address>(fp() + kWasmInstanceObjOffset + kSystemPointerSize));
3837 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, slot_base, slot_limit);

3935void WasmLiftoffSetupFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3936 FullObjectSlot spilled_instance_slot(&Memory<Address>(
3937 fp() + WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kInstanceSpillOffset));
3938 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "spilled wasm instance",
3939 spilled_instance_slot);
3940 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "wasm instance data",
3941 wasm_instance_data_slot());
3942
3943 wasm::NativeModule* native_module = GetNativeModule();
3944 int func_index = GetDeclaredFunctionIndex() +
3945 native_module->module()->num_imported_functions;
3946
3947 // Scan the spill slots of the parameter registers. Parameters in WebAssembly
3948 // get reordered such that first all value parameters get put into registers.
3949 // If there are more registers than value parameters, the remaining registers
3950 // are used for reference parameters. Therefore we can determine which
3951 // registers get used for which parameters by counting the number of value
3952 // parameters and the number of reference parameters.
3953 int num_int_params = 0;
3954 int num_ref_params = 0;
3955 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig =
3956 native_module->module()->functions[func_index].sig;
3957 for (auto param : sig->parameters()) {
3958 if (param == wasm::kWasmI32) {
3959 num_int_params++;
3960 } else if (param == wasm::kWasmI64) {
3961 num_int_params += kSystemPointerSize == 8 ? 1 : 2;
3962 } else if (param.is_reference()) {
3963 num_ref_params++;
3964 }
3965 }
3966
3967 // There are no reference parameters, there is nothing to scan.
3968 if (num_ref_params == 0) return;
3969
3970 int num_int_params_in_registers =
3971 std::min(num_int_params,
3972 WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedGpParamRegs);
3973 int num_ref_params_in_registers =
3974 std::min(num_ref_params,
3975 WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedGpParamRegs -
3976 num_int_params_in_registers);
3977
3978 for (int i = 0; i < num_ref_params_in_registers; ++i) {
3979 FullObjectSlot spill_slot(
3980 fp() + WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kParameterSpillsOffset
3981 [num_int_params_in_registers + i]);
3982
3983 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "register parameter", spill_slot);
3984 }
3985
3986 // Next we scan the slots of stack parameters.
3987 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code = native_module->GetCode(func_index);
3988 uint32_t first_tagged_stack_slot = wasm_code->first_tagged_parameter_slot();
3989 uint32_t num_tagged_stack_slots = wasm_code->num_tagged_parameter_slots();
3990
3991 // Visit tagged parameters that have been passed to the function of this
3992 // frame. Conceptionally these parameters belong to the parent frame.
3993 // However, the exact count is only known by this frame (in the presence of
3994 // tail calls, this information cannot be derived from the call site).
3995 if (num_tagged_stack_slots > 0) {
3996 FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_base(&Memory<Address>(caller_sp()));
3997 tagged_parameter_base += first_tagged_stack_slot;
3998 FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_limit =
3999 tagged_parameter_base + num_tagged_stack_slots;
4000
4001 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, "stack parameter",
4002 tagged_parameter_base, tagged_parameter_limit);
4003 }
4004}

4021
4022void JavaScriptFrame::Print(StringStream* accumulator, PrintMode mode,
4023 int index) const {
4024 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function()->shared(), isolate());
4025 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate(), shared);
4026
4027 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4028 Tagged<Object> receiver = this->receiver();
4029 Tagged<JSFunction> function = this->function();
4030
4031 accumulator->PrintSecurityTokenIfChanged(isolate(), function);
4032 PrintIndex(accumulator, mode, index);
4033 PrintFrameKind(accumulator);
4034 if (IsConstructor()) accumulator->Add("new ");
4035 accumulator->PrintFunction(isolate(), function, receiver);
4036 accumulator->Add(" [%p]", function);
4037
4038 // Get scope information for nicer output, if possible. If code is nullptr, or
4039 // doesn't contain scope info, scope_info will return 0 for the number of
4040 // parameters, stack local variables, context local variables, stack slots,
4041 // or context slots.
4042 Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info = shared->scope_info();
4043 Tagged<Object> script_obj = shared->script();
4044 if (IsScript(script_obj)) {
4045 Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(script_obj);
4046 accumulator->Add(" [");
4047 accumulator->PrintName(script->name());
4048
4049 if (is_interpreted()) {
4050 const InterpretedFrame* iframe = InterpretedFrame::cast(this);
4051 Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes = iframe->GetBytecodeArray();
4052 int offset = iframe->GetBytecodeOffset();
4053 int source_pos = bytecodes->SourcePosition(offset);
4054 int line = script->GetLineNumber(source_pos) + 1;
4055 accumulator->Add(":%d] [bytecode=%p offset=%d]", line,
4056 reinterpret_cast<void*>(bytecodes.ptr()), offset);
4057 } else {
4058 int function_start_pos = shared->StartPosition();
4059 int line = script->GetLineNumber(function_start_pos) + 1;
4060 accumulator->Add(":~%d] [pc=%p]", line, reinterpret_cast<void*>(pc()));
4061 }
4062 }
4063
4064 accumulator->Add("(this=%o", receiver);
4065
4066 // Print the parameters.
4067 int parameters_count = ComputeParametersCount();
4068 for (int i = 0; i < parameters_count; i++) {
4069 accumulator->Add(",");
4070 accumulator->Add("%o", GetParameter(i));
4071 }
4072
4073 accumulator->Add(")");
4074 if (mode == OVERVIEW) {
4075 accumulator->Add("\n");
4076 return;
4077 }
4078 if (is_optimized()) {
4079 accumulator->Add(" {\n// optimized frame\n");
4080 PrintFunctionSource(accumulator, *shared);
4081 accumulator->Add("}\n");
4082 return;
4083 }
4084 accumulator->Add(" {\n");
4085
4086 // Compute the number of locals and expression stack elements.
4087 int heap_locals_count = scope_info->ContextLocalCount();
4088 int expressions_count = ComputeExpressionsCount();
4089
4090 // Try to get hold of the context of this frame.
4091 Tagged<Context> context;
4092 if (IsContext(this->context())) {
4093 context = Cast<Context>(this->context());
4094 while (context->IsWithContext()) {
4095 context = context->previous();
4096 DCHECK(!context.is_null());
4097 }
4098 }
4099
4100 // Print heap-allocated local variables.
4101 if (heap_locals_count > 0) {
4102 accumulator->Add(" // heap-allocated locals\n");
4103 }
4104 for (auto it : ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
4105 accumulator->Add(" var ");
4106 accumulator->PrintName(it->name());
4107 accumulator->Add(" = ");
4108 if (!context.is_null()) {
4109 int slot_index = Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS + it->index();
4110 if (slot_index < context->length()) {
4111 accumulator->Add("%o", context->get(slot_index));
4112 } else {
4113 accumulator->Add(
4114 "// warning: missing context slot - inconsistent frame?");
4115 }
4116 } else {
4117 accumulator->Add("// warning: no context found - inconsistent frame?");
4118 }
4119 accumulator->Add("\n");
4120 }
4121
4122 // Print the expression stack.
4123 if (0 < expressions_count) {
4124 accumulator->Add(" // expression stack (top to bottom)\n");
4125 }
4126 for (int i = expressions_count - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4127 accumulator->Add(" [%02d] : %o\n", i, GetExpression(i));
4128 }
4129
4130 PrintFunctionSource(accumulator, *shared);
4131
4132 accumulator->Add("}\n\n");
4133}

4139void CommonFrame::IterateExpressions(RootVisitor* v) const {
4140 const int last_object_offset = StandardFrameConstants::kLastObjectOffset;
4141 intptr_t marker =
4142 Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
4143 FullObjectSlot base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
4144 FullObjectSlot limit(&Memory<Address>(fp() + last_object_offset) + 1);
4145 CHECK(StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
4146 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, base, limit);
4147}
4148
4149void JavaScriptFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
4150 // The frame contains the actual argument count (intptr) that should not be
4151 // visited.
4152 FullObjectSlot argc(
4153 &Memory<Address>(fp() + StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
4154 const int last_object_offset = StandardFrameConstants::kLastObjectOffset;
4155 FullObjectSlot base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
4156 FullObjectSlot limit(&Memory<Address>(fp() + last_object_offset) + 1);
4157 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, base, argc);
4158 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, argc + 1, limit);
4159 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), GcSafeLookupCode());
4160}
4161
4162void InternalFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
4163 Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = GcSafeLookupCode();
4164 IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
4165 // Internal frames typically do not receive any arguments, hence their stack
4166 // only contains tagged pointers.
4167 // We are misusing the has_tagged_outgoing_params flag here to tell us whether
4168 // the full stack frame contains only tagged pointers or only raw values.
4169 // This is used for the WasmCompileLazy builtin, where we actually pass
4170 // untagged arguments and also store untagged values on the stack.
4171 if (code->has_tagged_outgoing_params()) IterateExpressions(v);
4172}

4191InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry*
4192InnerPointerToCodeCache::GetCacheEntry(Address inner_pointer) {
4193 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(kInnerPointerToCodeCacheSize));
4194 uint32_t hash =
4195 ComputeUnseededHash(PcAddressForHashing(isolate_, inner_pointer));
4196 uint32_t index = hash & (kInnerPointerToCodeCacheSize - 1);
4197 InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry = cache(index);
4198 if (entry->inner_pointer == inner_pointer) {
4199 // Why this DCHECK holds is nontrivial:
4200 //
4201 // - the cache is filled lazily on calls to this function.
4202 // - this function may be called while GC, and in particular
4203 // MarkCompactCollector::UpdatePointersAfterEvacuation, is in progress.
4204 // - the cache is cleared at the end of UpdatePointersAfterEvacuation.
4205 // - now, why does pointer equality hold even during moving GC?
4206 // - .. because GcSafeFindCodeForInnerPointer does not follow forwarding
4207 // pointers and always returns the old object (which is still valid,
4208 // *except* for the map_word).
4209 DCHECK_EQ(entry->code,
4210 isolate_->heap()->GcSafeFindCodeForInnerPointer(inner_pointer));
4211 } else {
4212 // Because this code may be interrupted by a profiling signal that
4213 // also queries the cache, we cannot update inner_pointer before the code
4214 // has been set. Otherwise, we risk trying to use a cache entry before
4215 // the code has been computed.
4216 entry->code =
4217 isolate_->heap()->GcSafeFindCodeForInnerPointer(inner_pointer);
4218 if (entry->code.value()->is_maglevved()) {
4219 entry->maglev_safepoint_entry.Reset();
4220 } else {
4221 entry->safepoint_entry.Reset();
4222 }
4223 entry->inner_pointer = inner_pointer;
4224 }
4225 return entry;
4226}

4253UnoptimizedFrameInfo::UnoptimizedFrameInfo(int parameters_count_with_receiver,
4254 int translation_height,
4255 bool is_topmost, bool pad_arguments,
4256 FrameInfoKind frame_info_kind) {
4257 const int locals_count = translation_height;
4258
4259 register_stack_slot_count_ =
4260 UnoptimizedFrameConstants::RegisterStackSlotCount(locals_count);
4261
4262 static constexpr int kTheAccumulator = 1;
4263 static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4264 int maybe_additional_slots =
4265 (is_topmost || frame_info_kind == FrameInfoKind::kConservative)
4266 ? (kTheAccumulator + kTopOfStackPadding)
4267 : 0;
4268 frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ =
4269 (register_stack_slot_count_ + maybe_additional_slots) *
4270 kSystemPointerSize;
4271
4272 // The 'fixed' part of the frame consists of the incoming parameters and
4273 // the part described by InterpreterFrameConstants. This will include
4274 // argument padding, when needed.
4275 const int parameter_padding_slots =
4276 pad_arguments ? ArgumentPaddingSlots(parameters_count_with_receiver) : 0;
4277 const int fixed_frame_size =
4278 InterpreterFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize +
4279 (parameters_count_with_receiver + parameter_padding_slots) *
4280 kSystemPointerSize;
4281 frame_size_in_bytes_ = frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ + fixed_frame_size;
4282}
4283
4284// static
4285uint32_t UnoptimizedFrameInfo::GetStackSizeForAdditionalArguments(
4286 int parameters_count) {
4287 return (parameters_count + ArgumentPaddingSlots(parameters_count)) *
4288 kSystemPointerSize;
4289}

4291ConstructStubFrameInfo::ConstructStubFrameInfo(int translation_height,
4292 bool is_topmost,
4293 FrameInfoKind frame_info_kind) {
4294 // Note: This is according to the Translation's notion of 'parameters' which
4295 // differs to that of the SharedFunctionInfo, e.g. by including the receiver.
4296 const int parameters_count = translation_height;
4297
4298 // If the construct frame appears to be topmost we should ensure that the
4299 // value of result register is preserved during continuation execution.
4300 // We do this here by "pushing" the result of the constructor function to
4301 // the top of the reconstructed stack and popping it in
4302 // {Builtin::kNotifyDeoptimized}.
4303
4304 static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4305 static constexpr int kTheResult = 1;
4306 const int argument_padding = ArgumentPaddingSlots(parameters_count);
4307
4308 const int adjusted_height =
4309 (is_topmost || frame_info_kind == FrameInfoKind::kConservative)
4310 ? parameters_count + argument_padding + kTheResult +
4311 kTopOfStackPadding
4312 : parameters_count + argument_padding;
4313 frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ = adjusted_height * kSystemPointerSize;
4314 frame_size_in_bytes_ = frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ +
4315 ConstructFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize;
4316}
4317
4318FastConstructStubFrameInfo::FastConstructStubFrameInfo(bool is_topmost) {
4319 // If the construct frame appears to be topmost we should ensure that the
4320 // value of result register is preserved during continuation execution.
4321 // We do this here by "pushing" the result of the constructor function to
4322 // the top of the reconstructed stack and popping it in
4323 // {Builtin::kNotifyDeoptimized}.
4324
4325 static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4326 static constexpr int kTheResult = 1;
4327 const int adjusted_height =
4328 ArgumentPaddingSlots(1) +
4329 (is_topmost ? kTheResult + kTopOfStackPadding : 0);
4330 frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ = adjusted_height * kSystemPointerSize;
4331 frame_size_in_bytes_ = frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ +
4332 FastConstructFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize;
4333}
4334
4335BuiltinContinuationFrameInfo::BuiltinContinuationFrameInfo(
4336 int translation_height,
4337 const CallInterfaceDescriptor& continuation_descriptor,
4338 const RegisterConfiguration* register_config, bool is_topmost,
4339 DeoptimizeKind deopt_kind, BuiltinContinuationMode continuation_mode,
4340 FrameInfoKind frame_info_kind) {
4341 const bool is_conservative = frame_info_kind == FrameInfoKind::kConservative;
4342
4343 // Note: This is according to the Translation's notion of 'parameters' which
4344 // differs to that of the SharedFunctionInfo, e.g. by including the receiver.
4345 const int parameters_count = translation_height;
4346 frame_has_result_stack_slot_ =
4347 !is_topmost || deopt_kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy;
4348 const int result_slot_count =
4349 (frame_has_result_stack_slot_ || is_conservative) ? 1 : 0;
4350
4351 const int exception_slot_count =
4352 (BuiltinContinuationModeIsWithCatch(continuation_mode) || is_conservative)
4353 ? 1
4354 : 0;
4355
4356 const int allocatable_register_count =
4357 register_config->num_allocatable_general_registers();
4358 const int padding_slot_count =
4359 BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::PaddingSlotCount(
4360 allocatable_register_count);
4361
4362 const int register_parameter_count =
4363 continuation_descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount();
4364 translated_stack_parameter_count_ =
4365 parameters_count - register_parameter_count;
4366 stack_parameter_count_ = translated_stack_parameter_count_ +
4367 result_slot_count + exception_slot_count;
4368 const int stack_param_pad_count =
4369 ArgumentPaddingSlots(stack_parameter_count_);
4370
4371 // If the builtins frame appears to be topmost we should ensure that the
4372 // value of result register is preserved during continuation execution.
4373 // We do this here by "pushing" the result of callback function to the
4374 // top of the reconstructed stack and popping it in
4375 // {Builtin::kNotifyDeoptimized}.
4376 static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4377 static constexpr int kTheResult = 1;
4378 const int push_result_count =
4379 (is_topmost || is_conservative) ? kTheResult + kTopOfStackPadding : 0;
4380
4381 frame_size_in_bytes_ =
4382 kSystemPointerSize * (stack_parameter_count_ + stack_param_pad_count +
4383 allocatable_register_count + padding_slot_count +
4384 push_result_count) +
4385 BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize;
4386
4387 frame_size_in_bytes_above_fp_ =
4388 kSystemPointerSize * (allocatable_register_count + padding_slot_count +
4389 push_result_count) +
4390 (BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize -
4391 BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp);
4392}
